title: lemon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in light soy sauce for 1/2 hour. Prepare batter with flour, baking powder, egg and 1 cup water. Dip chicken in mixture and deep fry at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water and let cool. Save juice from pineapple. Mix 7-Up, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas together. Mix flour and sugar with pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Cook until thick and clear. Fold in whip cream and nuts. Add pineapple mixture and Jell-O. Refrigerate until thickened.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl. Put meat in slow cooker and put dry ingredients and water in. Cook until meat is tender and falls apart. Add more water if it is needed.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco. Add one egg at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa together. Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring. Put in a cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: seven can soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.	Drain.	Add all ingredients in a crock-pot.	Cook 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: ma's bundt cake
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, remove from oven.
Place a dish of same side on top.
Turn over; let cool.
Remove Bundt pan.
Serves a lot.
Enjoy!

title: mama crosby's biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 500°.
Use all fresh ingredients and no low-fat products.
This isn't the time to diet.
My grandmother said that the dough would feel right, look right and smell right. I only found that out after a lot of practice.

title: pie crust
directions: Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: buckeyes (candy)
directions: Mix
thoroughly,
then roll into small balls.
Melt one 12 ounce
bag	chocolate chips and 1/4 bar paraffin to smooth consistency.
Dip balls in chocolate with a toothpick, keeping chocolate warm.
Then refrigerate finished candy.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: venison roast
directions: Rub roast with A.1., salt and pepper.
Place meat in roasting pan.
Mix mushroom and onion soup together and pour over roast; add 1 soup can of water to pan.
Cover roast with foil, sealing sides of pan.
Cook 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8. Preparation Time:
3 to 4 hours.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 4 minutes.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!!

title: pie-buttermilk
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix well. Fold in 2 well-beaten egg whites and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cherry pie
directions: Start cold.
Drain juice from cherries into 1-quart pan.
Mix cornstarch (sprinkle).
Stir well.
Then under low-medium heat, add sugar and oleo.
Stir in dash of salt, then add cherries. Stir in lemon.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Cover with additional pie strips or slit top if using whole shell.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over butter and oats; let stand 20 minutes. Add sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Top with Butter Pecan Icing.

title: swedish hamburgers
directions: Combine bread, salt, paprika, pepper and milk.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in chuck and egg.
Shape into patties.
Melt margarine in skillet. Fry patties 4 to 5 minutes on each side at medium heat.
Remove from pan and place in a covered dish in a warm oven.
Saute onions in margarine and drippings remaining in skillet.
When onions are tender, sprinkle with flour.
Stir in milk and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Spoon over meat.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed on electric mixer until combined.
Gradually add egg substitute, beating well. Combine flour and salt with mixture running at low speed.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix these ingredients well.
Spread over hot baked layer and bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool; cut in bars.

title: sopaipilla cheesecake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Unfold one can of crescent rolls onto bottom of pan.
Blend together the cream cheese and sugar.
Spread the mixture over the bottom layer of the crescent rolls.
Then unfold the second can of crescent rolls over the cream cheese mixture.
Melt the stick of butter and pour over the layers.
Sprinkle the cinnamon/sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: morning market salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together first five ingredients.
Add vegetables; toss lightly.
Cover and chill approximately 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: down-home peach-raspberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

Toss peaches, raspberries, cornstarch and 1 tablespoon brown sugar in large bowl to mix well; set aside. Combine oats, remaining 2 tablespoons brown sugar, margarine, flour and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Mix with fingertips until crumbly.
Spread all but 1/4 cup of oat mixture over bottom of prepared baking dish; spoon fruit mixture over oats in an even layer.
Sprinkle remaining oat mixture over fruit.
Bake for 20 minutes until fruit bubbles and topping is browned.
Serve warm or at room temperature, accompanied by nondairy whipped topping.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut up carrots; cook in salted water, then drain.
Don't cook until soft.
Mix tomato soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Slice onion and bell pepper.
Add carrots, onion and bell pepper to mixture and leave overnight.

title: special broccoli
directions: Mix butter with broccoli.
Blend sour cream with mayonnaise and onion.
Put broccoli in greased casserole and top with layer of sauce, cheese and water chestnuts.
Top with cracker crumbs. Cook in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kolache
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the Solo fillings. Dough will be soft, but workable.
Roll dough in the palm of your hand into approximately 3/4-inch balls.
Flatten; place on cookie sheet.
Thumb indent and fill with a teaspoon of the filling.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Powder sugar tops when cool.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Fill empty can with milk.
Brown beef and onion.
Butter baking dish.
Place in layers, beef, vegetables, warm milk and chicken soup together.
Add top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes.
Reserve 1/2 cup carrot juice. Place carrots in shallow baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, parsley, carrot juice and salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.

title: kelly's brownies
directions: Get Mommy to drive you to store to buy brownie mix.
Wear clothes that can get messed up.
Get Mommy to sit you up on table with all ingredients.
If you are very careful, she will let you put ingredients in mixing bowl.
She will let you stir up the mix, but stir easy or it will run over sides of bowl.
Take spoon and put mix in brownie cups.
Put in microwave and bake according to directions.
Mommy always lets me push the buttons!
Let cool. Smear on icing.
Enjoy.

title: pepperoni and cheese rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough in 8 triangles.
Stretch each slightly.
Place 3 slices of pepperoni, slightly overlapping, on center of each triangle.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of cheese. Roll up.
Place rolls, point side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush rolls with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and set aside.

title: cheesy chicken-corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken, onion, celery and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Remove chicken, when cool enough to handle.
Cut off meat and chop.
Discard skin and bones.
Return meat to broth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream - lime sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve over hot or chilled cooked vegetables.

title: bootsie's layered salad
directions: In a flat 13 x 9-inch glass dish, place the ingredients in the order listed, pressing down each layer.
The salad dressing should be sprinkled dry over the mayonnaise layer, and lastly, cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set about 20 minutes.
Knead slightly and return to greased bowl to rise.
Place on floured board.
Knead lightly and divide into 2 parts.
Stretch section about 12 inches.
Cut strip into 10 pieces and mold into balls. Place on greased sheet and let rise one hour.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°
or until browned.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: jerky
directions: Mix ingredients. Add meat; soak 24 hours. Preheat oven to 250°. Bake 4 to 8 hours.

title: mushroom duxelles
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan and before the foam subsides, add the onion. Stir constantly over medium heat for 4 minutes without letting it brown.
Add mushrooms and cook until all moisture is absorbed (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle flour over.
Stir and pour cream over.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Stir in seasonings (not cheese) and cool. Refrigerate.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar and the egg.
Mix flour, baking powder and nutmeg together in another bowl.
Add the milk and flour mixture alternately to the shortening, sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Grease 15 medium muffin cups and fill 2/3rds full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix the 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon together.
Melt the margarine.
Immediately after baking puffs, roll them in melted margarine and then the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cauliflower in layers and place in deep dish. Spread mayonnaise on top of lettuce and cauliflower.
Sprinkle Ranch style dressing and Parmesan cheese on top of mayonnaise. Crumble bacon and chopped onion on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Toss before serving.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Cook rhubarb slow without sugar until rhubarb is soft and thoroughly cooked.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add to rhubarb and heat. Put in containers and freeze.
Keep in refrigerator after thawing.

title: puppy chow(microwave)
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir after 1 minute.
When smooth, stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over cereal stirring until all pieces are coated.
Pour cereal into large resealable bag with powdered sugar.
Seal well.
Shake well until all pieces are coated with powdered sugar.
Spread on wax paper until cool.
Makes 9 cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix dried skim milk and granola in bowl.
Mix in raisins and peanut butter.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: raspberry slump
directions: Heat fruit, sugar and water in a buttered 2 quart baking dish in a 400 degree oven.
Mix flour with baking powder, salt, and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Add milk, a little at a time, mixing after each addition.
Spoon over hot berries.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Try it with cherries or peaches as well, adjusting sugar to taste.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: ham and egg souffle
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, oleo and salt.
Put bread in pan, then cheese over bread, then ham over cheese.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour till light brown.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Arrange into a ball. Refrigerate and roll in crushed pecans before serving.

title: school days
directions: Mix orange juice and Kool-Aid with the specific amounts of water called for in their directions.
Mix all liquids together and freeze overnight to make punch slushy.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in large microwaveable container.
Heat on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and heat for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and heat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda and mix, then spread onto greased cookie sheet.
When cooled, break into pieces.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Beat just until combined.
Spoon into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole, sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: southern pralines
directions: Butter a sheet of foil.
Combine sugars, cream and salt in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture spins a thread about 2 inches long when dropped from a spoon.
Stir in butter and pecans.
Continue cooking until mixture dropped in cold water flattens when taken out.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes. Beat with a wooden spoon
until slightly thickened.
Drop spoonfuls onto foil.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter; saute onions and cornstarch and blend.
Add milk, salt and pepper and mix until thick.
Add crabmeat and cheese. Serve in chafing dish with Melba rounds.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 15-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken wings on the grill
directions: Marinate chicken wings in the Italian dressing overnight. Grill over low heat for 30 minutes; turn and grill 30 minutes more. Enjoy!

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix sugar and coffee granules with hot water and sprinkle over crumbled brownies.
In large compote dish or bowl, layer part of brownies, pudding mix, Cool Whip and crushed candy.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip and candy.
Chill until serving time.

title: dolores' shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In food processor, combine flour, salt and sugar. Add butter pieces and mix until batter begins to form a ball. Press evenly into 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
With a fork, prick shortbread all over, radiating evenly from center.

title: braunschweiger cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all.
Chill in Saran Wrap lined bowl 24 hours.
Turn out and frost with cream cheese, softened with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: "chicken lickin" good pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Place browned pork chops in crock-pot.
Add can of soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 1/2 hours.
Can cook in oven at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Can use chicken thighs or chicken breasts (skinned and browned).

title: chocolate chip peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In small bowl, cream peanut butter, margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until well blended.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Stir in 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread remaining chocolate chips on brownies.
When they become soft, spread with knife.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Fry ground beef and drain oil off.
Cook spaghetti and drain. Toss spaghetti in margarine.
Beat eggs and mix in Parmesan cheese. Mix with spaghetti.
Put spaghetti into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Pour Prego and spices into ground beef and simmer.
Pour sauce and meat mixture over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake for an additional 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into chunks. Combine with soups, carrots and peas. Prepare stuffing mix and spread over mixture in casserole dish. Cook at 400° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Drain and rinse peas.
Bring to boil with 6 cups water in large pot.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add rice and salt and continue cooking.
Meanwhile, saute garlic, onions and green peppers in oil.
Add the tomatoes, black pepper or cayenne and tamari.
Pour mixture into pot with rice and peas.
Stir to mix.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until rice and peas are tender.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Using a mixer on medium speed, combine first 3 ingredients together with 1 tablespoon of water.
Blend until smooth and pour into the graham cracker crust.
Let the cheese cake chill for 1/2 hour and spread cherry filling over cake and let it chill overnight.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (hands work well) and shape into a ball. (I sprinkle with paprika for color.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 14 1/2-inch).
Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and Bisquick in blender container. Cover and blend on high for 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese.
Cover and blend on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into plate and bake until center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cheese cake topping carefully over top.
Garnish with fruit.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together (except nuts) well and shape into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans or walnuts.
Chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop eggs, celery, carrots and onions.
Mix all ingredients (except macaroni).
Add to cooked macaroni.
Tastes better if it sets overnight.

title: broccoli dressing
directions: Cook fresh broccoli; drain off any water.
Add cream of chicken soup, butter, cornbread, sage and beaten eggs.
Mix well. Pour into dish.
Cook about 1 hour at 300°.
Melt cheese on top (optional).

title: scone
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients first.
Combine eggs, milk and margarine or butter (softened).
Add to flour mixture and mix until smooth.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix until evenly distributed.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in iron skillet.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit salad. Mix sour cream and milk. Pour over fruit. Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: strawberry-onion salad
directions: In blender, combine oil, vinegar, water, honey, poppy seed, salt, paprika and pepper.
Toss with lettuce, strawberries and onions and serve.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix well; this will be thick.
Pat with hand into 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.

title: sour cherry pie
directions: Mix together brown sugar, clear jell, cinnamon and almond extract.
Mix together with canned cherries and let set until pastry is prepared.
Makes 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: traditional meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a one-quart casserole dish, combine lime juice, water, garlic, chili powder, oregano and beef; cover with lid or foil.
Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat meat and tortillas at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until meat is thoroughly heated and tortillas are softened.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Add sweet milk and mix.
Sift the flour, soda and spices together. Add to the butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in the fruit and nuts. Add fruit juice last.
Bake at 325° until cookies are firm, but not brown.
These cookies may be kept for several weeks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, take off bone.
Cook spaghetti, drain.
Add butter, then mix soup, milk, cheese and chicken.
Stir until melted.
Bake at 325° to 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake roll
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs on highest speed of mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Fold in vanilla.
Gradually fold in flour mixture until smooth.
Butter bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; line with wax paper.
Butter paper and sides; dust with additional flour.
Spread batter evenly in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle a kitchen towel with confectioners sugar.

title: apple ring cucumber pickles
directions: Peel big cucumbers (too big for anything else).
Slice thick enough to make a good ring.
Cut out the centers.
This will be about 2 gallons of cucumbers.
Place slices in a stone container, sprinkle 2 cups of lime over them, add enough water to cover and let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash well, cover with ice; let stand 3 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into small balls. Refrigerate until just before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cranberry salad(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Place cupcake papers in muffin pans.
Fill cups.
Freeze in pans.
As soon as salads are frozen solid, remove papers and place in Ziploc freezer bags.
Keep in freezer.
Can be made well ahead of time. Serve frozen.

title: aunt dora's sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions with coarse chopper. Drain in colander.
Put in kettle (not aluminum).
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain again.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Cut chicken meat and ham into small pieces.
Add vegetables, bay leaf and broth.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Taste and add seasonings.
Remove bay leaf.
Pour hot mixture into hot sterilized pint jars.
Seal.
Process in pressure canner 65 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.
Process quarts 75 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Makes 12 pints.
I like to add rice to mine!

title: mexican corn bread(serves 8)
directions: Mix oil, sour cream, corn, eggs and milk together. Add meal, baking powder, salt, peppers, onion and 1 cup of cheese. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle the other cup of cheese on top. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: becky's blonde brownies(butterscotch brownies with chocolate chips on top)
directions: In large sauce pan, melt margarine.
Add sugar and blend thoroughly.
In small bowl, beat eggs until combined and add to margarine and sugar in sauce pan.
Add vanilla and blend.
In medium bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add 1/3 at a time, stirring thoroughly.
Spread into 13 x 9 pan which ahs been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with about a cup of chocolate chips. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, don't overbake!

title: spicy sausages
directions: Slice up hot dogs and smoked sausage.
Put into crock-pot with Little Smokies and picante sauce.
Let them simmer for approximately 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Simmer all seafood in clam juice 20 minutes.
Add chicken stock, whipping creme and wine.
Stir fry onions in butter till soft and then add to bisque.
Shake milk and flour together in a jar then add to bisque, slowly stirring till it thickens.
Add salt and white pepper.
Eat and Enjoy.

title: the best squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with sausage.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Soak the gelatine in the cold water.
Heat the whole milk hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cool, then add the cream.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and heat in microwave 2 minutes, stir. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda and stir.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Mix margarine with the crumbled Waverly crackers.
Place chicken pieces on crumb mixture in casserole.
Mix sour cream, chicken broth and cream of mushroom soup together; pour over the chicken. Top with the remaining crumb mixture and bake, uncovered, for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy tortilla bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. Line pan with tortillas, bringing edges of tortillas up even with the edge of pan.
Cook ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently, until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix (dry) and tomato sauce.
Spoon beef mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix in blender on high speed about 15 seconds or with wire whisk or hand beater for 1 minute until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and sour cream (if desired).
Makes 8 servings.

title: "you mix what to chicken?"
directions: Place chicken parts in casserole dish.
Blend dressing, preserves and onion soup; mix well.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Don't let ingredients scare you.
It's fabulous.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box and let set until slightly thickened.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish or pan; chill overnight or several hours.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown in large skillet the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in skillet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Last few minutes add Cheddar cheese on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into two oiled and floured 5 x 9-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 325° for glass.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Mix together butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add yeast mixture plus 1/2 cup warm water, salt and flour.
Mix all ingredients well and let stand in greased, covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Let rise at room temperature 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: apple pie pizza
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water over mixture, gradually.
Shape into a ball.
Roll pastry into 15-inch circle on floured surface.
Place on baking sheet; turn up 1/4-inch rim.

title: swedish cucumber salad
directions: Wipe cucumbers with fresh damp cloth.
Score cucumber skin with fork and slice very thin.
Place slices in bowl and sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Add vinegar.
Press slices until quite juicy.
Place in jars and refrigerate.

title: judy's cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Cook in preheated oven at 275° for about 30 minutes.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar while still hot.
Cookies will not be a dark color when done.
Delicious!!

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift the flour, salt and spices together and set aside.
Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine the applesauce and soda, then add to mixture.
Add the dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in the nuts and raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: three-bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook lima beans as directed on package; drain.
Turn into ungreased 4 1/2-quart bean pot or casserole. Add baked beans and kidney beans.

title: four-layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Cool.

title: johnnie cake
directions: Sift meal into a pan; make a hole in the middle and pour in water, adding salt.
With a spoon, mix the meal and water gradually into a soft dough; stir it very briskly for a quarter of an hour or more, until it becomes light and spongy.

Then spread the dough smoothly and evenly on a straight, flat board (a piece of the head of a flour-barrel will serve for this purpose); place the board nearly upright before an open fire and put an iron against the back to support it.
Bake it well; when done, cut it in squares.
Send it hot to table, split and buttered.

title: cool cucumber mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in combined water and vinegar; stir over low heat until dissolved.
Cool.
Gradually add gelatin to mayonnaise, salt and pepper; mix well.
Chill until partially set; fold in cucumber, whipped cream and onion.
Pour into oiled 5-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold; garnish with cucumbers and radishes, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and Italian sausage.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and place in casserole. Spread Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 300° until cheese is melted.
Parmesan cheese may be spread on if desired.

title: mushroom quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in quart jar and shake like H___!

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon.
Cook potatoes and barley separately.
Add everything else and bring to a boil.
Only need about 30 minutes after everything is added to cook.
If you use milk, add cornstarch to thicken.
If you use half and half, you probably won't need it thickened.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Beat thoroughly and put in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost when cool with vanilla or caramel frosting.

title: zucchini stuffed chicken quarters
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add zucchini and cook.
Stir frequently until tender (2 minutes); remove.
Into saucepan tear bread into small pieces.
Stir in egg, cheese, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Preheat oven to 400°. Push fingers between skin and meat to form pocket. Place stuffing inside each pocket.
Place chicken, stuffing side up in pan.
Bake 50 minutes.
Brush with honey.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: "sin" cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix nuts, margarine and flour together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass).
Pat down hard.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Slice 1/2 of cookie roll and lay side by side in pan.
Pour ingredients on top.
Lay rest of cookie slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pork spread
directions: Chop garlic and onions.
Put in pan over low heat with pork. When onions are soft, add cloves and cinnamon.
Salt and pepper. Cook over low heat for about 1 to 2 hours.
Add water as needed. After 2 hours, add saltines until saltines are absorbed, about 1 more hour.

title: sunday chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken and ham into bite size pieces.
In large bowl mix ham and chicken pieces, celery, mayonnaiae, sour cream, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Peel avocado and cut into bite size pieces.
Gently stir into chicken mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix sugar, tea, Tang, lemonade mix, cinnamon and cloves. Makes 1 quart.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Grease and flour a tube pan. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce, water, corn and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and margarine until it begins to simmer. Beat eggs until light and mixed well.
Add pecans to eggs.
After sugar, syrup and margarine comes to a simmer, add to eggs and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add pumpkin; add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon and bake in 350° oven.

title: "dirt pie"
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding.
Mix and beat.
Fold in Cool Whip, 1 cup cookie crumbs and the chips.
Place into crust. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over pie.
Freeze 4 hours before serving.

title: plain muffins
directions: Combine egg, milk and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix hot
water,
sugar,
salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in
warm
water.
Add eggs, flour, raisins and cinnamon. Stir until well
blended.
Let
rise
in warm
place about 50 minutes. Punch down.
Knead 1/2 minute.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Mix the crumbs with melted butter; reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into a 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan and chill.

title: mushroom cheeseburger pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place dough in greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan puff cookies
directions: Process flour and pecans until nuts are finely chopped.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until pale and fluffy.
With mixer on low, gradually add flour to mixture, just until blended.
Measure dough with teaspoon and roll into balls.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar. Cool completely.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Store in an airtight container for 2 weeks or can be frozen.

title: austrian green beans
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and gradually mix in cream and milk.
Add bouillon or a dehydrated chicken broth packet, stirring until thick.
Season to taste and add Swiss cheese.
Add green beans and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, corn syrup, eggs, melted butter and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat 30 seconds on medium speed.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Immediately arrange pecan halves on top.
Cool completely.

title: artichoke or asparagus dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and put in baking dish, cover top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top, about 20 minutes.

title: deer chili
directions: Cook all meat in a little oil until it browns, about 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except chili powder.
Cook on low heat 1 hour.
Add chili powder.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
It is better the second day.

title: no-bake skedaddles
directions: Mix well in large bowl, chow mein noodles and miniature marshmallows; set aside.
Combine in pan sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Bring to full, rolling boil, over high heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour over noodle mixture; stir until well coated.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into prepared 10-inch tube pan (a Bundt pan must be 10 inches and hold 12 cups; an angel food pan may also be used) and bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours until cake tests done.
Add glaze, if desired.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes before turning out.

title: melt-in-your-mouth cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and butter a 10-inch (1 1/2-quart) pie plate.
Arrange the cranberries on the bottom of the pie plate and sprinkle them with the nuts and 1/2 cup of the sugar.

With an electric mixer, beat the eggs and beat in the remaining 1 cup sugar gradually. Add the flour, butter and shortening. Beat the batter until smooth. Spoon the batter over the cranberry mixture and bake the pie in the middle of the oven for 1 hour or until the top is golden.

title: pot 'o' beans
directions: Stir-fry ground beef until done; drain.
In a 3-quart crock-pot mix all ingredients.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Stir and cook 30 minutes on low.

title: ranch enchiladas
directions: In large frying pan, crumble turkey and add picante sauce. Cook until turkey is done.
Spoon meat into flour tortillas and roll them up.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing together.
Pour mix on top of enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Very rich!
Makes 8 to 9.

title: baked country ham
directions: Soak whole ham overnight in cool water.
The next day, cut off hock end.
Place in a deep pan and fill halfway up with warm water. Cook in 300° oven allowing 20 minutes to the pound.
Remove skin while hot; make a mixture using 1/2 cup cornmeal and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pat all over top of ham.
Run back into a 450° oven and brown top of ham.
You may garnish ham with fruit if you prefer, but I like it plain and sliced thin and served on biscuits.

title: coconut pie
directions: Add eggs, sugar and flour; beat.
Add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: "apple kuchen"
directions: Mix and spread in greased shallow pan.
Peel and slice 4 medium apples as for pie.
Insert into dough mixture in rows, as closely as possible.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut thin slices of butter over all and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: t's homemade vegetable stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening until lightly browned in a large kettle.
Add all remaining ingredients except peas and cabbage. If using peas and cabbage (optional) pour into mixture about 5 minutes before stew is done.
Cook over medium to low heat for 3 hours (more or less).
Cook until potatoes and meat, etc. test done and stew has thickened and the flavors have had time to blend well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, orange slices, grapes and pecans. Set aside. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing mix. Mix well. Pour over chicken mixture and toss gently. Cover and chill at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute steak and onion.
Add sour cream, soup and spices. Simmer 20 minutes or until steak is tender.
May need to add milk or water to soup.
Serve over noodles.

title: broccoli with garlic and parmesan
directions: Combine water and garlic in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Wash broccoli thoroughly; trim off large leaves.
Remove outside layer of stem and the tough lower ends of broccoli stalks.
Separate into spears.
Add broccoli and salt to garlic mixture.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Discard garlic and drain broccoli well.
Transfer broccoli to a serving dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and Parmesan cheese before serving.
Serves 6 (36 calories per serving).

title: rice bake
directions: Into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish, put melted margarine; add onions, then rice.
Mix bouillon cubes, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over rice.
Add water will be absorbed when rice is done.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: tootsie roll
directions: Mix and knead together; then roll out into 3/4-inch rolls. Cut into lengths; let stand awhile and then wrap.

title: meringue
directions: Whip egg whites until peak forms; slowly add sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff peak forms.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: layered tortilla pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in butter.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper.
In round 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
At this point, cover pie and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Then, pour water at edge of casserole into bottom.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and allow to stand 5 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Sift together dry ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pans.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Either grind or put in blender.

title: molded cabbage salad
directions: Prepare jello as per directions on box.
When cool add cole slaw and dates.
Mold in individual molds or large bowl.
The cole slaw is prepared to suit your taste with green shredded cabbage, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Very tasty with fowl.

title: cole slaw(can be frozen)
directions: Combine cabbage and salt; let stand for 1 hour.
Add carrot and sweet pepper.
Boil together remaining ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour over slaw.

title: tequila lime punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine water, tequila, orange pineapple concentrate, lime juice and sugar.
Slowly pour lemon-lime beverage down side of bowl; stir punch gently with an up-and-down motion until mixed.
Float the lime and orange slices atop punch in bowl.
Serve over ice in punch cups.
Makes 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ham gumbo
directions: Lightly brown bacon; tear into pieces.
Lightly brown onion. Add all ingredients; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Cook mixture until okra is done, about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, blending well.
Stir in molasses.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating until smooth.
Place batter in 6 or 7 waxed paper lined 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 15-18 minutes.

title: graham muffins
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Add milk, beaten egg, sugar and melted shortening.
Bake in greased muffin pan for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and allow to cool completely.
Once chicken breasts are cool, cut into bite-sized pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add dressing until desired consistency is reached.
Miracle Whip can be substituted for slaw dressing.

title: broken glass
directions: Make 3 different flavors of Jell-O, using 1 1/2 cups hot water for each package of Jell-O.
Use shallow pans.
When Jell-O is set, cut Jell-O in cubes.

title: date muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl and stir in dates.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter from tablespoon into greased muffin pans. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put the sweet potato slices in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, spreading them over a bottom crust if you like.
Mix together the ginger, both kinds of sugar and the flour and sprinkle them over the potatoes.
Dot the potatoes with the butter and add the water.
Place a crust over the potatoes and bake for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together the flour, melted butter and nuts.
Press in pan. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen uncooked, then thaw in microwave for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch and water and pinch of salt.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Whip eggs and milk.
Mix sugar and flour; add to egg mixture. Add margarine and rhubarb; blend.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large.

title: peanut butter waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until almost smooth.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes; then remove from pans and cool completely.

title: chocolate-chip cake
directions: Prepare topping:
In small bowl, mix brown sugar, walnuts and 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate mini pieces; set aside.

title: cran-apple salad
directions: Place cranberry sauce in a glass casserole dish.
Mash with a fork.
Grate apples (using amount desired) over sauce.
Stir in. Spread with desired amount of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate for a soft salad.
Freeze for a solid salad.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Mix egg and milk in bowl. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Simmer in soup for 15 minutes.

title: honey bear chicken
directions: Put chicken into baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, mustard and mustard seed.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots on the bias; cook in salted water until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile combine next 4 ingredients in a small saucepan. Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Boil one minute.
Stir in margarine.
Pour over cooked hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 1/2 x 12-inch utility dish.
Put in apples; sprinkle with sugar.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Beat 3 minutes and pour into greased pan.
Put 1 cup coconut on top.
Let set for 5 minutes, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine in a heavy saucepan, mixing well, then over medium heat, bring to a rolling boil.
Now, reduce heat (do not stir) and cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°F or 112°C); cool to lukewarm (110°F).
Now, beat until thick.
This won't take very long.
Spread fudge in an 8-inch pan and, when cool, cut into squares.

title: hamburger hash brown hot dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with hash browns.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Place on top of hash browns.
Add a layer of peas and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over the top.
Place cheese slices on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and sprinkle onion rings on top.
Return to oven with heat off for 15 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and refrigerate.
Keeps well for several weeks.
Shake well before serving.
Serves 6 (regular) people or 1 Irishman.

title: bay state breakfast muffins
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Set aside.
Grease muffin tin.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Add cranberries, carrots and nuts to apple mixture and stir gently to combine.
Mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Stir well.
Stir in eggs and oil and mix gently.
Divide among muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cook for 5 minutes in pan and remove to wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: charlotte aux pommes
directions: Cook and stir bread crumbs in butter over medium heat until toasted.
Mix sugar, lemon peel, cinnamon.

title: pickled onions
directions: Peel onions.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
Put in colander and rinse thoroughly with cold water to remove all salt. Drain. Tie spices loosely in a bag.
Boil 10 minutes with vinegar and sugar. Discard spices.
Pack onions in hot sterilized jars. Pour hot vinegar mixture over onions.
Seal at once.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Slowly add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into cooled baked shell and spread top with meringue.
Put a little coconut on top and brown meringue.

title: individual ham balls
directions: Combine meats, crumbs, eggs and milk.
Mix well and form into balls.
Mix soup, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Boil slowly until thickened.
Pour over meat mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together cocoa, sugar, flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix together boiling water and baking soda.
While still fizzling, pour over flour mixture.
Blend.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla (or mint extract).
Beat for 2 minutes.
Place in greased pan.
Bake about 35 minutes.

title: blueberry gook
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham crackers.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Layer in dish, starting with graham cracker mixture, Cool Whip mixture and blueberries, ending with Cool Whip mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small rolls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before cutting.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except vanilla and cinnamon sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add vanilla. Spoon into dessert dishes and sprinkle cinnamon-sugar on while hot.
Chill and serve cold.

title: penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt until tender.
Mix all the ingredients together and set in icebox overnight.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12-cup fluted tube pan (Bundt pan) with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons nuts over bottom of prepared pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits; cut each biscuit in half and shape into a ball.
Place 20 balls in bottom of prepared pan.
Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over balls.
Repeat layers.

title: country fair chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour, and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in 11
1/2 inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken; bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: grilled salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 4 or 5 patties.
Place on grill and cook on low for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter while cooking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in margarine onion, bell pepper and celery, about 5 minutes.
Mix with cooked rice, milk, cream soup and Cheese Whiz. Spray casserole dish with Pam cooking spray and turn rice mixture into dish.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: white punch
directions: Put in large saucepan and let simmer the sugar, water and rinds from the lemons and oranges for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: red plum sauce
directions: Pit plums and slice them fairly thin.
In a medium saucepan, stir together plums, sugar and 1 cup water.
Simmer about 15 minutes, until plums are soft.

title: bread dough ornaments
directions: Other materials needed are aluminum foil, cookie sheet, craft wire, paints, paintbrush, fine tip permanent marker, sharp knife, varnish and garlic press.

title: lemonade
directions: One serving:
2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 3/4 cup water.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Press half the crumbs into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with 4 cups of cut up rhubarb (other fruit may be used in its place).
Cook the second mixture until it is thick and clear and pour over the rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or golden.
Cut into squares and serve while warm.
Whipped cream or ice cream is optional.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Poke some holes in them.
Bake in microwave for 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes over; bake for 10 more minutes.
Take out and cut in half.
Melt butter in microwave.
In a baking pan place the potato halves.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add Manwich and cook juice down. Drain beans and mix in skillet. Add ketchup and brown sugar. Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in muffin pans for 15 minutes at 400°.
Mixture will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Crumble sausage and fry.
Drain.
Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spray pan with Pam first.
Beat eggs; add Bisquick and milk.
Beat with fork.
Do not use mixer.
Add grated cheese, saving some for top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: microwave pineapple pie
directions: Drain juice off pineapple; add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups in a large bowl that is safe for microwave.
Put sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix together and add 1/2 cup liquid.
Beat until smooth, then add eggs and beat until the eggs are well beaten. Then add the other 2 cups liquid and beat again.
Put in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Take out and beat.
Then give it another 2 minutes and do the same.
It takes about 8 minutes in all but sometimes it may take a little longer.
But it is important to beat it good after every 2 minutes.
When stiff enough, beat in oleo.
Pour into 9-inch baked crust.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add garlic.
Stir and cook until soft and golden, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings and tomato products.
Bring to a boil at medium-high heat, then reduce to low, cover loosely and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add ground chuck if you want meat sauce.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook over medium heat to 232° or thread stage.
Add pecans, stirring until cooled and mixture is creamy. Pour onto greased platter or waxed paper.
Separate nuts while cooling.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix with eggs and juice from fruit cocktail.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake at 300° in three layers for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Brown meat in oil.
Saute peppers and onions in meat grease.
Mix sugar, ginger, cornstarch and water.
Add mixture, tomatoes and meat. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in roaster pan and cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.
If desired, add carrots, potatoes or favorite vegetables in preferred amounts.
Cover and bake another 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are done.
Remove cover last 15 minutes to allow juices to thicken.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tarragon cream of chicken soup
directions: Heat the chicken stock for 5 minutes.
Add the tarragon leaves.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Cook a bag of Ramen noodles as directed on bag.
Put in 2 bowls and serve.

title: baker's best coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes about 18 macaroons.

title: chocolate chunk-n-nut brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar, add melted margarine, stir well, beat in eggs; mix well.
Blend in flour, vanilla, nuts and chocolate chunks.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes or until done.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat in flour and spices; mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli and cheese puff
directions: Grease 9-inch baking pan. Cook chopped broccoli in boiling, salted water according to package directions; drain well. Cut 4 slices bread into triangles and line pan. Combine broccoli with butter, Swiss cheese, salt, Tabasco and minced onion. Spoon over bread. Beat eggs; add milk, then pour over broccoli mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until puffed and set.

title: denver muffins
directions: Boil water.
Add dates until softened.
Add oil.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add the dry mixture to the date mixture.
Mix well, then add vanilla.
In muffin tins with baking cups, fill with batter 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Pick off bones and put aside.
Save broth. Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
Put a layer of dressing (about half) into baking dish.
Put chicken over this.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour both cans of soup diluted with 1 can of broth over chicken (this should be mixed together first in separate bowl).
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 2 tablespoons warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and other dry ingredients.
Cut shortening in this flour mixture and add 1 cup of the buttermilk; add yeast and the other cup of buttermilk.
Mix well.
Blend on floured board.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
Will keep 1 week.
Take out amount needed, roll 1/2 inch thick and cut out biscuits.
Dip in melted butter and bake 15 minutes at 400°. Dough does not need to rise.

title: rhubarb delight(rhubarb makes a good cobbler dish.)
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in oleo and stir in egg and milk.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover this with rhubarb and sprinkle the gelatin on top.
Next, top cobbler with crumbly mixture and then bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: garlic herb bread
directions: Slice bread dough (thaw 1/2 hour to 45 minutes) into 15 to 16 pieces. Dip bread slices into butter mixture. Let all excess butter drip off. Layer in well-greased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan. Let rise to top of pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Flip over onto plate and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve while warm.

title: mountain pie
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart dish or pan.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this mixture over melted butter (do not stir); then add fruit and juice (do not stir).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart shallow dish and cover with marshmallows while warm.
Let congeal, then frost with sour cream. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: mcdougal salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add onion, tuna, pickles, salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade sour cream
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy.

title: green chili sauce
directions: Cook pork in a little water until tender, about 1/2 hour.
In hot oil in a skillet, cook pork (drained and cut up) until lightly browned.
Add garlic and onion; cook until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in pork stock; bring to a boil, stirring over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, uncovered, and stir about 5 minutes.
Serve over burritos.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery in skillet.
Add soup, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat over low heat to serving temperature.
Serve over noodles.

title: eggplant main course
directions: Saute ground beef until it is nearly cooked.
Slice veggies except for eggplant.
If eggplant is tender and fresh, leave skin on and cut in cubes.
(If not, peel it.)
Spray a casserole dish with Pam.
Combine veggies, meat, Italian seasoning and some of the grated cheese; pour into casserole dish.
Do not add Mozzarella yet.
When your casserole is cooked, 350° for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours, sprinkle with grated cheese and top with Mozzarella.
The heat from the food will melt the cheese, also good without meat sauce.

title: german dumplings
directions: Combine ingredients to form stiff dough.
Spoon into boiling salted water or bouillon about 5 minutes each side.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts one hour.
Let cool.
Cook bunches of asparagus and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cut chicken and tortillas into bite-size pieces.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, seasonings and lemon juice.
Mix two cheeses together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish from the bottom to top:
asparagus, chicken, tortilla, soup mixture, cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, butter the tops of 8 patties and arrange to fit baking dish.
Butter the tops of 8 more patties and lay on top of the bottom 8 patties.
Shake well the pint of whipping cream, then pour over patties.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover, stir and bake an additional half hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Use electric skillet; quick fry steak.
Add pepper, margarine and onion.
Cook on medium heat, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and water.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes, covered, or until potatoes are done.

title: red punch
directions: Mix water, Kool-Aid, juice and sugar.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, place frozen mixture in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Best when slushy.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add 1/2 of sifted dry ingredients.
Add mincemeat and water; stir until blended. Add nuts and remaining flour mixture; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil 3 cups sugar and 6 cups water for 3 minutes.
Then cool. Mix remaining ingredients together for fruit base.
(Can put bananas in blender with some of the juice to mash.)
Combine cooled syrup and fruit base.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve. All but the ginger ale can be frozen and then allow 3 to 4 hours to thaw.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: crackle sauce
directions: Cook walnuts in butter until crunchy.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Serve over ice cream.
(It will harden on contact.)
Enjoy.

title: english muffin and crab appetizer
directions: Melt cheese with margarine and crab.
Smear on muffins. Freeze 2 hours.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Heat in broiler 3 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan.
Place sliced apples in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is brown. Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, vegetables and juice.
Cook 45 minutes on low.
Delicious for a cool day.
Freezes well.

title: chunky vegetable-beef soup
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in a 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with browning powder. Microwave (High), uncovered, 4 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink.
Add carrots, celery, onion, garlic, bay leaf, water and bouillon.
Cover with lid.
Microwave (High) 7 to 8 minutes, or until mixture boils.
Stir, then microwave (Low, 30%) for 30 minutes, or until vegetables are just about tender. Combine cornstarch with some of liquid from tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and cornstarch to hot soup, stirring well.
Salt and pepper.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread on tortillas. Sprinkle on pepper, olives and celery.
Roll tight and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, break up ground beef.
Add tomato paste, tomato juice, water, chili powder, garlic salt, salt, sugar, oregano and minced onion.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
Add spaghetti; stir to separate strands.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: farewell chili
directions: Cook brisket 3 hours.
Grind brisket, peppers, onion and garlic using meat grinder.
Brown in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add sage to taste, chili seasonings, stout and tomatoes.
Puree in food processor.
Add to meat.
Cook in oven covered 20 minutes.
Remove cover and add beans and let cool.
Reheat to serve.

title: doc's stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, garlic and onion in oil.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook noodles in water and bouillon cube.
Serves beef mixture over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Pour oil into deep heavy saucepan.
Dredge beef with flour and brown beef in hot oil.
Remove beef and set aside.
Add water, wine, soup mix, chili sauce and pepper.
Stir well.
Return beef to pan.
Bring to simmer and simmer for 1 hour.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain.

title: chicken in coke
directions: Combine equal amounts of ketchup and diet coke to make sauce to cover chicken.
Cook until tender and chicken falls apart (about 1 hour).
Use sauce over mashed potatoes.
If adding optional vegetables, put in at same time as chicken.
This sauce works with pork chops also.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse noodles.
Marinate vegetables.
Add noodles.
Add Salad Supreme seasoning (amount to taste).
Chill until served.
(Can use curly, shell, macaroni or linguine style noodles.)

title: saundra's cabbage salad
directions: Arrange ingredients in layers in a large container.
Do not stir.

title: tomato tuna chowder(heart smart)
directions: In oil, saute onion, garlic, celery and green pepper.
Add potatoes and water, boil 20 minutes.
Add tuna, tomato juice, cayenne pepper and poultry seasoning; cover and boil ten minutes longer.
Serve.

title: crispy brown sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven 375°. Line two baking sheets with parchment and set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter until smooth. Add sugars and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together, then slowly beat dry ingredients into wet mixture. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop 2 to 3 tablespoons of dough per cookie onto prepared baking sheets; space dough at least 2-inches apart to allow for spreading. Bake until golden, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from baking sheets and allow to cool on racks. Makes 4 dozen (4-inch) cookies.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put spices in bag.
Bring vinegar, spices, sugar and salt to a boil.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a rolling boil. Cook about 2 minutes and turn off heat.
Wait 1 hour and jar.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Beat eggs 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Blend until moistened.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° about 38 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Scrape and cut carrots into thin strips.
Place carrots in a deep 1/2-quart heat resistant, microwavable dish.
Set aside.
In a small microwavable bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power for 1 minute or until butter is melted. Spoon butter-sugar mixture over carrots.
Heat, covered, on Full power for 7 minutes.
Spoon sauce over carrots and heat, uncovered, on Full power an additional 3 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put everything together.
Cook in 350° oven for 15 minutes uncovered.
Stir and continue cooking uncovered for total of 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: myrna's chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Pat out in oblong dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie crust.
In medium pan, over low heat, heat chocolate with butter or margarine just until melted; remove from heat.
Add sugar and next 6 ingredients with hand beater or wire whisk; beat until well mixed.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour mix into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes, until filling is puffed.
Cool.
Serve topped with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: macerated fruits
directions: Remove cores or stones from fruits and slice or halve according to size.
Sprinkle lemon juice over any fruit likely to brown.
Arrange in layers in large glass dish.
Add sugar to wine and pour over fruit.
Leave in refrigerator for several hours or overnight to allow fruits to macerate.
Serve with cream.
Serves 12.

title: sauerkraut marinated salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
In a separate bowl, mix oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple.
Add cold water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into jello.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Combine cottage cheese and 1/2 jello in small bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 c. pineapple. Fold remaining pineapple into clear jello.
Spoon half of clear jello into 6 cup mold.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over clear layer.
Spoon remaining jello over cottage cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: baked fish almandine
directions: Combine and pour over fish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup blanched slivered almonds on fish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with orange or lemon slices.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Mash the potatoes, mixed with the other ingredients, until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into lightly greased casserole; cover tightly and refrigerate for later use in planning a dinner when you need to save time.
Will last up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
When ready to use, uncover, sprinkle top with paprika and dot with butter and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: good corn bread
directions: Mix, bake in grease in an iron skillet.
Very good.
No oven temps or times were given in 1948!
Suggest 400° for about 22 minutes.
M.N.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and pour into an already made graham cracker pie crust.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: company casserole
directions: Prepare noodles in salted water according to package directions.
Brown ground beef in 3 tablespoons butter.
Drain. Add tomato sauce and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
In a medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese and green onion.
In a large casserole dish, layer 1/2 of noodles, then cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over noodles.
Put meat sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly and add sugar, salt, lemon juice and peel.
Cook until mixture coats spoon.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Bring orange juice to boil and pour over orange jello and stir until dissolved.
Blend egg mixture and gelatin mixture together and cool.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until whites hold stiff glassy peaks. Fold in the cooled gelatin egg mixture and add diced cantaloupe, folding it in carefully.
Pile into baked pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.
May top with whipped cream.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Mix pizza sauce, cheese, garlic salt and oregano with ground beef mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour together; pour on top of meat and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in your slow cooker crock-pot.
Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cream cheese crab ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then mix powdered sugar, wine, mustard, Old Bay and onion powder.
Add crabmeat.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 6 hours.
Roll into 2 balls; roll balls in crushed pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: grandma curtin's famous rice crispy chicken
directions: Roll out Rice Krispies until they are very finely crunched up.
Dip chicken parts into melted butter or margarine.
Then roll chicken parts into crunched up Rice Krispies.
Place in baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: campfire cake in an orange
directions: Prepare cake mix and directed on box.
Cut off the top of the orange (about 1/3).
Save for lid.
Spoon the fruit out of the bottom 2/3 of the orange, leaving empty shell.
Fill shell 1/2 full with cake batter.
Place lid back on orange.
Wrap entire orange in aluminum foil.
Place in coals of campfire for 10 to 12 minutes. Eat out of shell.
One orange per serving.

title: grandma claire's pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 c. butter at 325 degrees for 25 minutes. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream one cup of soft butter.
Slowly add sugar to butter, until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Beat in dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into three 8 inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, salt and milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and yeast. Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.
Cover.
Let stand in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Toss on a floured surface until no longer sticky.
Roll out dough on floured surface to a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Brush with margarine.

title: mocha angel food cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to package directions.
Chill other ingredients in metal bowl with beaters.
Whip until mixture is consistency of whipped cream.
Ice cake when cool with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese clusters(microwave)
directions: In
a 2-quart glass pitcher, melt chocolate and butterscotch chips
on
Medium-high for 2 minutes, or until melted. Stir
until smooth.
Stir
in	noodles
and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.	Let set until firm.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except onions. Pour into crust and top with onions. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. You may substitute green onions and green peppers in the mix and omit fried onions on the top.

title: french dressing
directions: Place ingredients into mixing bowl. Blend slowly for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onions and bell pepper. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chili seasoning mix. Add shredded cabbage with 2 to 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer until cabbage is cooked to your liking.

title: mom's lazy blueberry pie
directions: Melt
the
margarine
in
a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix milk, sugar and
flour	and
pour over margarine.
Pour blueberries over mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Flour will rise to top. Whipped topping may be used when served.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Cover rhubarb with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Cream sugar and shortening, add egg and beat well.
Fold in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chili cups
directions: Spray two sets miniature muffin tins with nonfat cooking spray.
Place won ton skins in muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from tins and place on cookie sheets.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chocolate chips with shortening, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in raisins and almonds. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until ready to serve. Makes 2 dozen.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Combine 1/4 cup butter and cracker crumbs into a 9-inch pie pan.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.	Place in crumb shell. Top
with
eggs
beaten
with
the	milk and the salt. Sprinkle with
cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious with bacon or sausage.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Remove from heat; stir in powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and flavoring. Mix well and cool thoroughly.
Shape into balls about the size of a quarter and chill.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 7 minutes over low fire.
Serve with French bread.

title: peach-apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine 10 cups thin sliced pared apples and peaches, spices, sugar and flour into mixing bowls. Turn several times and allow the ingredients to rest and mingle while preparing the pastry.
Carefully place the ingredients into a pastry lined glass pie plate.
Build the mound from the rim up to the center.
Clip the excess pastry to within 1/2-inch of the pie plate.
Add lemon drops and butter.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and egg.
Add pineapple juice and cook until thickened.
Add butter and fold in.
As mixture cools, fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Spread over top of set jello and sprinkle with nuts.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and nuts; beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When done, spread with 1 large jar of marshmallow cream on warm cake.
