Cool well. Frost with the following frosting.

title: grilled game hens
directions: Mix all spices.
Rub all over hens.
Grill until juices run clear, about 15 minutes a side.

title: upper peninsula pasties
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in suet or lard.
Add milk.
Knead dough.
Divide into 12 balls.
Roll each into a 6-inch circle.

title: squash fritters
directions: *Season-All may be used instead of pepper.

title: coconut date bars
directions: Combine dates, water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Sift together flour and salt; stir in brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Press 1/2 crumb mixture in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with the filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top and press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: crab soup
directions: Dissolve soup mix in water.
Add crab liquid and whipping cream.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in crabmeat and wine.
Heat. Serve warm.

title: jacky's broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Drain.
Put in ovenproof square baking dish. Mix milk and soup and pour half over broccoli.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle half of onion rings on top of soup.
Add Cheddar cheese and mushrooms and remaining soup.
Bake, covered with foil, for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out and add remaining onion rings on top.
Bake for 10 more minutes, uncovered.

title: sharon's chili chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper, garlic powder, ginger and oregano.
Dot with butter and brown on both sides under broiler. Sprinkle with oregano.
Saute mushrooms in butter and garlic powder.
Combine sherry and chili sauce in saucepan and simmer for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, green pepper and mushrooms to chicken and pour sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Baste often with juices.

title: pink punch
directions: Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: macaroni salad with crab meat(cookbook winner)
directions: Place macaroni in a medium bowl.
Add onions, celery, crab meat, mayonnaise, salt, and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: italian baby stuffed eggplants
directions: Wash eggplants with cold water.
Cut off stems and discard. Cut eggplants in half lengthwise.
Scoop out inside of eggplant very well.
Saute garlic in olive oil until slightly brown.
Add to frying pan scooped out mixture of eggplant and saute until soft. Remove from frying pan.

title: sara's stir-fry rice
directions: Put oil in skillet and heat.
Add carrots for 5 minutes.
Then add peas for 5 minutes.
Add onions and green pepper.
Stir-fry 10 minutes.
Add broccoli pieces for 5 minutes.
Drain the oil off.

title: quick cornmeal muffins(low-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the cornmeal, whole wheat flour, unbleached flour, baking powder and sage.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, egg, honey and oil.
Pour over the dry ingredients and mix well.
Coat 12 muffin cups with nonstick spray.
Divide the batter among the cups, filling them about halfway.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix beef, taco sauce, refried beans, peppers, onions and ketchup together.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Spread into 2 pie plates or square pans.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Use chips of your choice.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Beat all of the ingredients, except wafers, together for 5 minutes.
Place vanilla wafers in bottom of muffin baking cups. Pour filling into cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate before serving and top with favorite pie filling.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Spread butter on one side of each tortilla.
Combine the next 5 ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up each tortilla and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
To serve, cut in 1/2-inch slices and serve with salsa.

title: banana-pineapple yogurt shake
directions: In blender, combine ingredients except ice.
Blend until smooth.
With blender running, add ice cubes, one at a time through opening in lid, blending until slushy.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 94 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1/2 cup Milk, 1 Fruit.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix well green beans, Shoe Peg corn, sour cream, celery soup, onion and grated Cheddar cheese.
Spread in greased casserole dish.
Combine melted butter, Ritz crackers and slivered almonds and spread over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello-shots
directions: Boil water.
Use 1 cup of water and 1 cup of liquor.
Mix and pour into 1 or 2 ounce plastic cups with lids.
Chill until set.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in the oil; when the vegetables are just transparent, add sausage slices and brown lightly.
Add beef stock and all other ingredients.
Bring soup to a boil, stirring to keep the bottom of the pan from burning.
Reduce heat.
Allow to simmer for 35 to 45 minutes or longer if you like, stirring occasionally.
Correct seasonings to taste.

title: wrap-around cherry cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cherries.
Wrap small amount of dough around well-drained cherries.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Use cherry juice to make powdered sugar icing or glaze.
Makes 20 to 25 cookies.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk; spread over sliced cake.
Sprinkle pecans over the cheese layer. Spread Dream Whip over nuts.
Mix pie filling and extract together and pour over whipped cream.
Chill overnight.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Work all ingredients into dough, except Reese's miniature peanut butter cups.
Put small amount of dough (not even a teaspoonful) into greased miniature muffin tins.
Push down flat. Do not line sides of tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Drop a miniature peanut butter cup into the middle of each muffin tin as soon as they come out of the oven.
Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry. In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, chestnuts and green onions. Cover. Refrigerate 2 hours. Stir before serving. Make be served in a hollowed out round loaf of bread.

title: easiest ever ice cream
directions: Stir together well. Freeze firm. Break up and whip until fluffy.

title: golden fried shrimp
directions: Butterfly shrimp and wash under cold running water.
Combine egg and salt in a shallow bowl.
In another container, combine flour and cracker crumbs.
Dip each shrimp in egg mixture, then roll in cracker mixture.
Repeat procedure.
Heat oil until 365°. Fry shrimp for 2 or 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until blended.
Serve warm with Guiltless Gourmet no oil tortilla chips.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, almonds, onion, cheese and salt.
Add juice and mustard to mayonnaise.
Fold into chicken mixture.
Put into casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; sift flour and add salt and resift.
Add to creamed mixture, working it thoroughly with fingers.
Work in vanilla and nuts (or coconut).
Chill about one hour, then roll about one-inch in diameter.
Cut one-inch lengths and roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven for about 14 to 17 minutes, or until lightly brown. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: dry yeast rolls
directions: Stir sweet milk, sugar and shortening together and bring to a boil.
Set off and cool to lukewarm.
Add flour and dry yeast.
Let rise until double in size and add 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Sit in refrigerator in covered bowl and use as wanted. Shape and let rise out of refrigerator until high and light before baking.

title: carrot balls
directions: Cream the cheeses and apple juice concentrate.
Stir in carrots.
Form into small balls and roll balls in chopped nuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put alternate layers of drained beans and onions in a casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and basil; pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Arrange 1 inch pieces of bacon on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together.
Heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add the strawberry jello mix.
Put in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Mix with strawberries.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add soda, salt, flour and buttermilk. Mix well. Separate eggs. Set aside egg whites. Add yolks and coconut to batter. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Grease and flour 3 cake pans. Pour batter evenly into pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top and done inside.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges and oil.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: virginia dare cookies
directions: Bring to boil first 2 ingredients. Add peanut butter and Special K. Mix well and drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Stir together bread crumbs and butter.
Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix together soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash.
Combine stuffing and melted butter.
Put 1/2 stuffing mixture in baking dish.
Add squash mixture; put rest of stuffing over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam.
Heat over medium-high heat. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Starting with skin down, brown chicken for about 15 minutes, turning once.
Add chopped onion and green pepper and cook for 2 more minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, thyme, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Heat to boil, spooning sauce over chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: savory roasted onions
directions: Mist the onions with the nonstick spray and sprinkle them with the savory.
Place cut side down in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° until tender, about 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with the vinegar and parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Place all the ingredients in a 3/4 pan.
Cook, covered, on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Turn occasionally.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the blueberry preserves and water together.
Spread the following layers in this order: pineapple, blueberry mixture, dry cake mix, melted margarine and pecans.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until brown on top. Let sit 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies into crumbs.
Set aside.	Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar and set aside.
Mix milk and pudding and add cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a bowl or large plastic flower pot, begin layers with cookies and pudding, ending with cookies on top.
Let set for a few hours.
Serve cold.

title: hot bean casserole
directions: Cut up bacon; brown with onions.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five-minute fudge
directions: Combine butter or margarine, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat. Stir in marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts until marshmallows are melted.
You could substitute chocolate pieces for butterscotch pieces.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take chicken out of kettle and add water for broth for dumplings.
Put flour in bowl. Add milk and shortening.
Dough will be thick.
Drop by teaspoon in boiling broth.
Cover and cook on low 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables and spaghetti salad
directions: In large mixing bowl combine first five ingredients.
In a screw top jar combine vinegar, the 3 Tbsp. oil, sugar, lemon juice, parsley, basil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and shake well;
pour over vegetable mixture. Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours. Meanwhile cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Toss with the 1 Tbsp. olive oil.
Cover and chill.
To serve, spoon vegetables around spaghetti in lettuce lined bowl.
Toss before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: m&m color cookies
directions: Mix well. Bake at 375°.

title: flavored ice tea
directions: Boil water in a large saucepan.
When rapid boil is reached, turn off heat.
Put tea bags into the water and cover.
Let steep about 1 hour.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix first 3 ingredients to form soft dough. Drop by 9 spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Mix butter and garlic powder; brush generously over warm biscuits. Makes 9 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, add Jell-O, sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel and section oranges over a bowl to save juice.
Slice bananas; add to the oranges.
Quarter the cherries; mix with the oranges and bananas.
Toss.
Place in serving containers; sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in pie crust.
Pour mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at least 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Mix all other ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: caramel dip for fruit(apples)
directions: Blend together, serve at room temperature.
Slice apples to serve with dip.

title: quiche pie
directions: Add chopped ham to bottom of uncooked pie crust.
Beat eggs by hand.
Mix flour with small amount of half and half to make it smooth.
Add milk and milk-flour mixture with eggs.
Add cheese and salt and pepper.
Mix well with wire whisk or fork; pour over ham.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for approximately 40 minutes, or until almost set.
It will shake slightly in middle.
Let it cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Must be served hot.
Serves 8.

title: margie's peppers
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large pot.
Place washed, whole peppers in boiling water.
Watch and cook until the peppers are tender but firm to touch.
Remove peppers and cool.
When cooled, slice them about 1/2-inch in thickness.
Be sure to remove the seeds and stems.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Add sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Add flour a small amount at a time until dough is
easy to	handle.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Put them in a shallow dish. Pour the milk over them.
Soak for 30 minutes turning twice.
Mix flour and salt in a plastic bag.
Add onion rings a few at a time to coat well.
Heat Crisco to 325° in deep saucepan.
Fry onion rings for 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: decorator cake icing
directions: Mix vanilla, meringue powder and Crisco for 3 to 5 minutes in a mixer.
Add sugar and half of water; moisten at low speed.
Add remaining water and mix 6 to 8 minutes.
Recipe will frost one 9 x 12-inch layer cake or two 8-inch round layers.

title: chicken devine
directions: Heat chicken, soup and add mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese.
Add bread crumbs to melted butter.
Arrange chicken breasts over broccoli in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Place buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole #4
directions: Place
squash in a dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over squash and crumbs.
Top with the rest of the crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries and reserve half of best ones.
Mash the other half, add cornstarch and sugar and cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool add whole berries, or, if too large, cut in half, but save a few for garnishing.
Pour into pie shell, cover with whipped cream and garnish.

title: mustardy oven baked chicken(diabetic or regular meats)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine mustard and egg with a whisk until well blended.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs and stir well.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then dredge in crumb mixture.
Let stand at room temperature on waxed paper for 10 minutes to set coating.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done and coating is lightly browned.

title: party mix
directions: Mix the oil, worcestershire, garlic and seasoned salt well in a blender.
Mix all other ingredients together in a large bowl. Pour some of the oil mixture over dry ingredients, stir and repeat until well mixed.
Bake in 250 degree oven for 2 hours stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peggy's stew
directions: Use Dutch oven pan.
Cover bottom of pan with oil and brown ground beef.
Cut up celery and pepper and add to stew along with frozen vegetables and sweetened tomato wedges.
Add enough water to fill half of pan.
Add desired amounts of seasonings.
(I add generous amounts of each for a flavorful aroma.)
Add beef bouillon cubes.
Simmer about 1 hour.
When cooked, thicken stew with 3/4 cup flour and water.
Serves 4 (one bowl apiece).

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a bowl, cream together sugar and shortening with mixer until light.
Add eggs one at a time, and milk beating until smooth and fluffy.
Add flour and bananas alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Gently fold in the nuts.
Pour batter into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and place in bottom of 30-cup percolator.
Put last 3 ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk as for coffee.
Makes 30 (6 ounce) servings.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend sugar and flour.
Add to eggs.
Add margarine, vanilla, milk and coconut.
Put into two small or one large greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar; mix well.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: baked apple dessert
directions: Melt margarine and spread to coat sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel and core apples.
Soak 1 hour in water to which lemon juice has been added.
Drain.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and walnuts.
Place
apples in baking pan and cover with cinnamon mix. Bake
covered
for
30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, and flour.
Beat the eggs, and add the rhubarb and flour mix to the eggs.
Bake in a
9 inch pie crust at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: apple food cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, then apples.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Batter
will be stiff.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake
1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Cool before slicing.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Make jello and let congeal. Mix milk and mayonnaise together. Add all other ingredients and pour into jello.
Very good with ham loaf.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Melt shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
(Cool enough to not cook egg.)
Beat until well mixed.
Add other ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Make 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on greased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes, until cracks appear on top, at 375°.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Drain shrimp.
Rinse; drain well.
Pour shrimp in with cream cheese; mix together well.
Make a ball and chill.
Pour cocktail sauce over to cover.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: marinated garden tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes and onions in a shallow serving bowl. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over tomatoes. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: spicy cherry sauce for ham
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Add undrained cherries, spices and food coloring.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and cloves. Serve warm with ham.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate beef, chicken or pork for 6 to 8 hours.
Grill or broil.

title: double dutch pizza cookie
directions: Cream butter & sugar until light & fluffy.
Beat in egg & vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Slowly add to creamed mixture, mix well.
Lightly grease foil on a pizza pan. Spread dough to 1/2 inch from edge.
Evenly sprinkle with candy & marshmallows.
Bake at 350 degrees for 18-20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on one ham slice.
Repeat with remaining mixture and ham slices.
Roll up from short sides.
Chill for several hours or wrap and freeze if desired.
To serve, slice rolls into 1/2-inch thick slices. Arrange slices on top of crackers.
If frozen, let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before serving.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and put sugar over them. Grind orange and apple. Combine with cranberries. Mix Jell-O with boiling water. Mix with other ingredients and add chopped nuts. Pour into bowl and refrigerate to set.

title: nassi(indonesian dish)
directions: Fry leek mushrooms and onion in vegetable oil for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken, shrimp and chili pasta.
Fry again for about 5 minutes.
Add the cole slaw at the last minute.
Fry the cooked rice in vegetable oil and sojasauce for 5 minutes.
Combine mixture with the rice and heat well for a little while (keep stirring).
Add sojasauce to taste.
Side dish:
Fried egg with a slice of ham.

title: layered salad
directions: Then let stand for 45 minutes or until no grains of sugar are seen.
Put mixture on top of the cheddar cheese.
Then fry 1 lb. bacon and crumble on top of mixture.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a large greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking dish in oven.
Remove from oven and add mixture of flour, sugar, milk and vanilla flavor.
Drop peaches evenly in this mixture but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pat on sides and bottom of greased spring-form pan.
Soften cream cheese in a large bowl, gradually adding eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Must be smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Turn off heat and let cake stay in oven for another hour. Do not open door until one hour has passed.
Let stay in spring-form pan until cool.
Refrigerate.
If desired, top may be sprinkled with crust mixture or after baking, you may spread cherry, pineapple or blueberry pie filling on top.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix in blender and then freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: sweetheart fudge pie
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Melt chocolate over hot (not boiling) water.
Add to creamed mixture with coffee and rum flavoring.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool.
Whip cream stiff.
Fold in cherries.
Spread on top of pie.
Decorate with chocolate or candy hearts.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In greased casserole dish, put half the macaroni and mix with 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put 1 cup cheese over this.
Put other half macaroni, 1 1/2 cups cheese and dot with the other 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix the eggs, salt and milk and beat well.
Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle top lightly with paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until macaroni is bubbly and set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a vanilla wafer crust.
Strawberries may be added to top, if desired.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix well the pecans, oleo, milk and powdered sugar.
Form into walnut size balls. Put on wax paper and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, melt the canning wax and chocolate morsels in a double boiler.
Dip balls in this mixture and let set on wax paper.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package lime jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water; let jell.
Drain juice from small can of fruit cocktail and heat.
Thoroughly mix the cream cheese with salad dressing.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix all ingredients (fruit cocktail juice, cream cheese, salad dressing and Knox gelatine mixture) until smooth.
Pour on top the lime jello mixture; let jell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Combine all remaining ingredients; add broccoli.
Cook in casserole dish for 30 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch pan generously and dust with flour.
Blend all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Can use a 9-inch pie dish.
Use fresh or frozen strawberries on top.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend with a fork.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift the 2 cups flour and the confectioners sugar.
Cut in the butter until mixture clings together.
Press in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Beat together the eggs, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Sift together the 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake in a 350° oven 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and onion in Dutch oven.
Chop cabbage.
Add cabbage to Dutch oven and cook until done.
Cover, adding pepper to taste.
Cook noodles.
Combine noodles and cabbage mixture. Serve hot.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix
altogether
and pack into cookie sheet; melt large Hershey candy bar and pour over top.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, water, rice and 1/2 can onions.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture and sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: chili con carne
directions: Fry meat and onion in shortening until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Blend well and add milk and dry ingredients.
Put in cold oven; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: lettuce dip
directions: Place in blender 1 cup of the lettuce, salad dressing, green onion and seasonings.
Blend until smooth.
Continue to blend while adding the remaining lettuce and cubes of cream cheese. Blend until smooth.
Chill.

title: french toast deluxe
directions: Mix syrup, eggs, milk and salt in shallow bowl.
Dip bread into mixture; drain slightly.
Saute on both sides in shallow hot fat. Serve hot with additional Log Cabin syrup (try it warmed).

title: pecan clusters
directions: Place marshmallow cream and kisses in a large bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil, then cook for 8 minutes.
Pour over marshmallow cream and kisses, stirring until well blended.
Stir in pecans and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: mr. bill's chili
directions: Brown the meat and onions together; drain grease.
Add the tomatoes that have been churned up in the blender.
Also add the tomato sauce, salt, chili powder and pepper.
To the side, cook spaghetti and gradually add to the meat mixture.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Put cottage cheese into bowl.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over it and stir.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: yummasette
directions: Toast 1/2 loaf of bread in butter.
Mix all the soup and cream together.
Add to the other ingredients which have been put in a large container.
Mix.
Pour into a roast pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, beat margarine, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt. Add to sugar mixture. Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets onto wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: herbed breast of chicken
directions: Cut 4 small slits in onion and insert a clove into each slit. Set aside.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together melted margarine, sugar, nuts and flour. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Let cool and press down.

title: zucchini scallop
directions: Put all ingredients into pan. Cook until done and juice is cooked down.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix dressing and serve on lettuce.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour.
Mix together margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no-bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk and brown sugar for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: family favorite french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixer bowl.
Add salt, butter and flour.
Using a dough hook mix until well blended, about 2 minutes. Mix on medium speed 2 minutes longer.
Turn out on floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm, draft free spot about 1 hour.
Punch down and divide in half.
Roll each half into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Roll up dough tightly, tapering ends.
Place loaves on greased baking sheet on top of cornmeal.
Cover; let rise 1 hour.
Make 4 cuts across loaves and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Beat egg white with water, brush on loaves and bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool on wire racks.

title: irish stew
directions: Cut meat into squares and cook slowly until tender.
Add vegetables.
Thicken with a little flour mixture.

title: vegetable bars(a nice change from sweets at parties or office functions.)
directions: *Thawed frozen vegetable medleys can also be used to save time and are more digestible.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Cut up large head lettuce in large bowl.
Add everything else and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly. Arrange apples in shallow, well-greased pan. Sprinkle apples with dry mixture and cover baking dish. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until apples are tender. Remove cover and bake a few minutes longer until crumbs are brown.

title: stuffed dill pickles
directions: Cut crusts from bread; place between damp tea towel (until bread is soft, but not wet, approximately 10 to 15 minutes). Blend the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread cheese mixture on bread slices.
Wrap around a large dill pickle.
Wrap tightly with Saran Wrap; repeat as many times as you need.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove plastic wrap and slice thin to serve.

title: chili cheese spread
directions: Make sure your cheese is at room temperature.
Heat milk to boiling; pour over cheese in mixer bowl.
Beat until nearly smooth.
Add butter and garlic; beat well.
Stir in green chilies (mixture will be thin).
Chill.
Serve as spread for fancy crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups of spread.

title: porcupine balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, add hamburger, rice, eggs and spices. Mix well.
Roll into golf-ball size balls.
Place in a large saucepan.
Cut bell pepper into strips and onion into rings.
Add to saucepan.
(If you like spicy foods, at this time, add more spices.)
Cover with tomato juice.
Cook over medium heat until balls are done in middle, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and drain off any fat.
Brown bacon (do not drain).
Add catsup, sugar and vinegar in baking dish or roaster large enough for all ingredients).
Add all beans.
Stir. Simmer in oven at 350° for 1 hour or cook on low in crock-pot.
You can leave out green beans for a different taste.
Serves a large family.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in rest of the ingredients. Mix flour in 1 cup at a time.
Knead dough until almost not sticky.
Put in buttered bowl. Cover and let rise 30 minutes. Punch down.
Divide into 2 balls (add flour to hands as it will be sticky). Shape dough onto greased pizza dishes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Place in blender and mix well.
Store in tightly covered jar. Keeps for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups or use paper liners.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine brown sugar, buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in rhubarb and walnuts.
Add to flour mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into cups.
In small bowl, with fork, blend granulated sugar with butter.
Sprinkle some over muffin batter in each cup.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Mix. Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of skillet.
Pour enough milk to barely cover.
Salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat until milk boils.
Place several slices of oleo on top.
Turn to low heat and cover.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Just before serving, top with grated cheese and allow to melt.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in 2 eggs one at a time.
Mix in flour.
Stir in nuts.
Spread 3/4 mixture into 13 x 9-inch ungreased Pyrex pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Take remaining batter and drop by spoonfuls.
Spread as well as possible.
Bake for 45 minutes or until light brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix all together.
Makes three (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: spanish chicken with rice
directions: Combine and simmer 45 minutes.

title: crock pot meat
directions: Put all ingredients in a 8 quart slow cooker for 24 hours. Shred an serve on buns.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook cornmeal and milk until thick.
Add salt, sugar, shortening and egg yolks (well beaten).
When thoroughly blended, add baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 400° in well-greased baking dish for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Into a bowl sift the flour twice with the baking soda, the ground ginger, the cinnamon and the mace.
In a food processor blend the butter, 1 cup of the sugar, the gingerroot, and the rind for 5 seconds, add the egg, and pulse the motor until the mixture is just combined.
Add the molasses and pulse the motor until the mixture is just combined.
Add the flour mixture, blend the mixture for 8 to 10 minutes.
Pinch off chunks of the dough, each about the size of a cherry, roll them into balls, and roll the balls in the remaining 1/3 cup sugar, coating them well.
Arrange the cookies 3 inches apart on lightly buttered baking sheets and bake them in batches in the middle of a pre-heated 375 degree oven for 10 - 12 minutes or until they are browned lightly.

title: banana cake
directions: After mixing cake, add banana.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch oblong pan.

title: crusted crispy baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken, pat dry and set aside.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In
another	bowl,
mix potato flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan
cheese.
Roll chicken first in egg and milk mix. Then roll
in
potato
flakes mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Roll	coated chicken in the butter and place skin side up in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Transfer to platter. Garnish with celery leaves and slices.
Serve.

title: carrot cake and cream cheese icing
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add oil and blend well. Add carrots and vanilla.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 3 (8 or 9-inch) round cake layers.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together shrimp, cream cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Salt to taste.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add jam.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water; mix well just before putting into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: green stuffed peppers
directions: Mix meat with catsup and sauce.
Stuff peppers and arrange in casserole.
Pour the tomato soup and water over the peppers and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Baste with the juice while baking.

title: fontenot's sugared popcorn
directions: Pop and place in large pot.
Do not salt.
Heat 1 cup of water.
Pour 2 cups sugar and boil until sugar starts forming on rim of pot.
Pour contents into pot, holding popcorn and stir while pouring.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish and place broccoli spears on the bottom.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder to make a sauce and pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes or microwave until hot.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch metal pan, line with one can of dinner rolls (pressing seams together and working dough out to cover bottom of pan).
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and flavorings.
Spread over rolls.
Cover with other can of rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring to boil; 3 cups water and salt.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add peas, cauliflower, broccoli and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Blend flour with small amount of milk until smooth and add to vegetable mixture with remaining milk and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley when serving.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimento; mix well.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together cold and store in covered container in refrigerator. Will keep for weeks.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate chilled cheese. Mix well with other ingredients. Shape into small round balls or long rolls. Coat each in chili powder. Slice rolls and serve with chips.

title: sunday night skillet supper
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
In separate skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Add hash browns, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeping the skillet over low heat, pour eggs over mixture in skillet.
Sprinkle sausage over eggs.
Cover and cook until eggs are set, about 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: healthy apple-walnut muffins(from great american home baking cooking series)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 standard size muffin pan cups or use paper liners.
Beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Alternately stir flour mixture and buttermilk into egg mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Do not overmix batter.
It should not be completely smooth.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook juice, eggs, sugar and flour until thick.
Add butter and pineapple; cool.
When cool, add small marshmallows and bananas.

title: self-rising buttermilk biscuits
directions: Place flour in large bowl.
Make a well in center of flour. Add milk and oil.
Mix with spoon (you may need more or less milk) and turn out on well floured board or waxed paper.
Knead lightly. Pat 1/2 inch thick.
Cut.
Turn biscuit top and bottom side in very well oiled 9x13 baking pan.
Bake at 500 degrees until golden brown.
Makes 9-12 biscuits.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: For cocoa mix, stir together milk powder, nondairy creamer, cocoa powder and Equal.
Cover and store in airtight container. For each serving, in a heat-proof mug, add 3/4 cup boiling water to 1/3 cup cocoa mix.
Stir to dissolve.
Makes 2 2/3 cups mix (eight 6 ounce servings).
Diabetic Exchange:
1 Milk.

title: pork and rice casserole
directions: Combine meat, rice, vegetables and soup in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Cover and bake with microwave for 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water until done.
Drain and mash.
Whip in cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Add milk if necessary. Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish or 2 smaller dishes. Cover and refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to use, drizzle melted butter over potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° for 40 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes, uncovered, to give nice golden brown top.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Peanuts will be browned and syrup very hot. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: butternut snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour with salt and add to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add pecans and mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet.
Bake in slow 325° oven for about 20 minutes.
Do not allow to brown. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange tapioca
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until done.
Add salt, extract and orange.
Refrigerate until cool.
Serve with low-fat whipped cream substitute.

title: "killer" chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine oil, water and egg.
Add to cake mix and mix until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Mixture should be firm and have a shiny texture.
Drop by 2 tablespoons onto cookie sheet, leaving room for them to spread as they bake. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: soft sorghum cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift together first 4 ingredients. Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix in shortening, sugar, sorghum and egg until creamy.
Mix in soda and all but a few raisins or nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with remaining raisins.
Bake 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheese strata provencal
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper together, then pour over the first 5 ingredient mixture. Chill overnight in an 8 x 11-inch casserole (greased).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 50 minutes until lightly browned and center is firm to the touch. Cool 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: veggie burger
directions: Combine lentils, bread crumbs, egg whites, spinach, carrots, onions, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Shape into 6 equal patties.
Place on baking sheet.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: irish coffee torte
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, except substitute coffee for water.
Bake cake in 2 round layer pans. Cool for 10 minutes.
Prick top of layers with wooden pick and sprinkle each layer with about 2 tablespoons Irish whiskey.
Beat whipped cream and sugar until stiff.
Pipe between layers and on top.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: carrot ring
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and carrots.
Grease ring pan.
Put in pan 1/2 cup Wheaties.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan of water up to 1/3 side of pan.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cracked wheat raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water water.
Combine cracked wheat, raisins, sugar, salt, margarine and 2 cups boiling water.
Cool to 110°.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add 2 cups flour and beat 2 minutes. Stir in 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil unopened cans of condensed milk for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from stove top and allow to cool.
After cans are cooled, open and spoon caramel into pie crust.
Put in freezer and chill.
After it has set, cover with Cool Whip.

title: de-e-licious cookies
directions: Put graham crackers on cookie sheet lined with foil over the sides.
Melt butters; add sugar and bring to a boil.
It will be foamy.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Easy and quick.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Cook beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add chili powder and salt.
Stir in tomato juice, beans, rice and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes (covered).
Top with cheese and cover until cheese melts. Spoon over Fritos.

title: quick fix salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into patties. Put small amount of oil in skillet and fry. Brown both sides. Quick and easy.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch metal pan.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl and pour into pan over margarine.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake cornbread.
Boil squash until tender and drain.
While squash is still hot, add oleo; stir and melt.
Add cornbread, onion, soup and pepper.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: white christmas sugar cookies
directions: Put soda in buttermilk and don't use more than 4 cups of flour. Cream the Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients; mix.
Make a day ahead of time and put in refrigerator. When ready to use, roll out medium amounts of dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Do not roll real thick.
Bake only 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: To prepare:
Place breast halves between sheets of waxed paper.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side. Do not cook longer or they will be dry.
Place chicken breasts on warm serving platter.
Add green onions, parsley and mustard to pan; cook for 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth. Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter or margarine and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken on serving platter. Serve immediately.
Good served with noodles or macaroni with tomato sauce, steamed broccoli or other green veggies and a fresh salad.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze.
Set aside.
Soften cream cheese. Beat cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice. Make in layers, starting with vanilla wafers and ending with strawberries on top.

title: monkey buns
directions: Preheat
oven
to
While
oven
is heating, melt butter in 8-inch pie pan.
Add brown sugar, syrup, spices and nuts.
Mix into
paste, evenly covering bottom of pan.
Pinch each
biscuit into 3 pieces.
Arrange on top of syrup-nut mix. Bake
12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert on 8-inch plate.
Serve hot or warm.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: maki's pound cake
directions: Use 2 bowls to mix this cake.
In bowl #1, cream butter and flour.
In bowl #2, cream eggs and sugar, then mix the 2 batters together.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Increase heat to 325° for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: hot punch
directions: Simmer in slow cooker and serve hot.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter or margarine with sugar and lemon juice in small skillet.
Drain carrots and place in sugar mixture.
Heat for about 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ganny's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until you can insert a knife and it comes out clean.
Let cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: roly-poly lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare noodles as directed on package. In a bowl, combine cheeses, egg, spinach and salt; mix well. Place one lasagna noodle on work surface and spread 1/2 cup of the mixture over the noodle.
Roll up.
Continue with remaining noodles. Spread 1 cup of tomato sauce over bottom of baking dish. Place in noodles, seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over center of each noodle.
Cover with foil, bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley and serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time. Combine flour, soda and salt and add alternately with sour cream to the sugar mixture.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and coconut extract.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.

title: e-z meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put in bowl.
Add ketchup on top.
Cook at 170° with probe until done (approximately 15 minutes at #1).
Let stand about 10 minutes.

title: golden chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer (skin-side down) in shallow baking dish.
Dribble butter over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken; bake 20 more minutes.
Stir soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake for 20 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger hoagies
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, then add Italian style peppers.
Turn heat on stove to low; simmer about 10 to 15 minutes. Fill hoagie buns with hamburger and peppers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add onions, spices and mayonnaise.
Toss to mix.
Fold in eggs carefully.
Chill.

title: easy choco frosting
directions: Cream together shortening, egg, cocoa and salt.
Add sugar alternately with milk and vanilla.
Blend until smooth and creamy.

title: ham and apple saute
directions: In a wok or large skillet, heat butter and ham.
Remove ham. Add onions and apples.
Add ham back in with jelly and mustard. Serve with/over rice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill milk until icy (2 1/2 hours).
Add water to jello and chill until syrupy.
Beat milk until thick and add jello, a little at a time.
Cream the cream cheese with the vanilla and sugar. Whip all together.
Pour in crust and refrigerate.

title: ham and cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Cut slice from stem end of peppers, remove seed and cook in boiling salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine ham, stuffing, parsley, pepper, tomatoes and onions.
Take 2 slices of cheese and cut into 6 strips. Repeat with 2 more slices.
Place 3 strips upright in each pepper. Cube remaining cheese and stir into ham mixture.
Pile into peppers.
Place in shallow pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with salt in water to cover until almost tender. Drain.
Add cheese and milk to hot potatoes. Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake in 275° oven until bubbly and thick, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Blend flour until mixture holds together.
Press firmly into 14-inch round pizza pan or 15 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spread melted morsels over top.
Arrange pecans, cherries and coconut over top.

title: bar cake
directions: Cut bread into 3 to 4 horizontal slices.
Spread blended cheese and other goodies on each layer and stack.
Melt cream cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Glaze the stack to make it appear as white frosting.
Can use color dyes.
Decorate with thin sliced onion or chives greens, cherry tomatoes, olives, parsley, etc.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry sauce(brandied)
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in 1-quart glass bowl or measuring bowl. Stir in lemon juice and crushed strawberries. Cook, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil is clear, in microwave.
Cool slightly. Stir in brandy to taste. Chill well before serving. Use over cake or ice cream.

title: cinnamon syrup
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, heat butter, syrup and cinnamon until butter is melted. Stir until smooth. Serve warm over pancakes, French toast or waffles.

title: tomato relish
directions: Bring the vinegar, spice and sugar to a boil.
Mix with other ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Pour in clean jars and seal.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in baking dish.
Whisk remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour half over chops.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chops and pour rest of seasonings over.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: beans with pork and tomato sauce
directions: Wash dry beans.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours in cool place.
Drain beans.
Cover with boiling water. Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain. Put about 1 cup beans in hot jar.
Add small piece of ham or pork. Fill jar about 3/4 full with beans.
Add tomato sauce to within 1-inch of top.
Process pints 65 minutes, quarts 75 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: foolproof chicken
directions: Mix the soups, wine and rice together in casserole dish.
Let stand several hours.
Arrange chicken breasts over top and cover. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and stir.
Cook 1 hour longer.

title: cho-cherry cake
directions: Blend cake using only the eggs and pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter with 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Add powdered sugar and graham crackers.
Pour into pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Press into pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread over the top.

title: easy cheesy cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter.
This will be stiff.
Pat into oiled and floured 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour this over cake in pan. Top with nuts.

title: porcupine meatballs(microwave)
directions: Mix together beef, rice, 1/2 can tomato soup, egg, water and onion salt.
Shape into 12 balls.
Arrange in a circle in a 9-inch pie plate (glass).
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 7 to 9 minutes.
Spoon topping over meatballs.

title: perfect fudge
directions: Using low heat, stir and mix cheese with margarine (knead these).
Let cool for 2 minutes.
Add cocoa, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Knead all of the mixture until smooth.
Line pan with wax paper.
Mash into pan. Store in airtight can. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: guacamole
directions: Beat all but tomato in mixing bowl.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: french pastry
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as pie dough and pat in 2 strips on cookie sheet.
Bring oleo and water to boil and remove from heat. Stir in remaining flour and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Spread on top of first strips.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar icing flavored with vanilla.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill 8 x 8 pan with apple pie filling. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle Jiffy cake mix over apples and pour melted butter and milk over cake mix.
Lightly blend cake mix, butter and milk with a spoon.
Bake for 20 minutes then slightly stir crust.
Bake another 20 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
This is great with ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunch drop cookies
directions: Drop and bake at 350°.

title: liver-bacon-potato casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet, drain and crumble.
Pour off most of fat.
Add onions to skillet and saute. Push aside.
Add liver and cook until brown and done.
Remove liver and cut in cubes.
Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour. Gradually add milk and cook until thickened.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put liver, onions, potatoes and 1 cup crumbled bacon in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add sauce and mix well.
Mix remaining bacon and cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheerwine cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute 1 cup Cheerwine for water and add almond extract.
Pour into pan and bake as directed.
Frost immediately with Cheerwine Frosting.

title: penny's cranberry marshmallow salad
directions: Combine and chill overnight the cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
The next day, add remaining ingredients to mixture and chill.

title: chicken
directions: Pour dressing and apricot preserves over cut up chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into balls. Freeze on cookie sheet.
Bake frozen at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until completely blended and smooth. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown around edges, 12 minutes or so.

title: wild plum muffins
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes in miniature muffin pans.
Makes 96 small muffins.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set the oven at 350°.
Cream together the oleo and peanut butter.
Beat in sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, salt, baking soda and flour. Press with a fork dipped in flour after dropping by tablespoons on cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all together.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour with half of milk until creamed. Add eggs, remaining milk, water and butter. Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thick. Add vanilla and cool. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: u. s. senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water and cover.
Drain beans and put them in a soup kettle with hambone and water.
Bring water to boil and simmer the mixture for about 2 hours.
Stir in 1 cup mashed potatoes, onions, celery, garlic cloves and parsley.
Simmer the soup for 1 hour longer or until beans are thoroughly cooked. Remove hambone from kettle.
Dice the meat on it and return meat to soup.
Serves 6.

title: hungarian cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread thin with jelly. Add remaining mixture for the top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fancy sliced tomatoes
directions: Put a layer of sliced tomatoes in shallow bowl; cover with layer of thinly sliced onions.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, pinch of basil, 1/2 teaspoon sugar, 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon olive oil.
Repeat layers and seasonings until you have as many layers as you want.
Let stand in refrigerator for a few hours. Serve as is or place on bed of greens.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown beef and sausages.
Drain off excess grease.
Add spices and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted, mixing well.
Spread mixture on split bagels.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with orange juice in mixing bowl until smooth.
Fold in marshmallow creme.
Serve dip in center of large glass plate surrounded by fresh fruit.

title: richard's chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs, vanilla and melted margarine and stir well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight to let flavors blend.
Serves four.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Prepare a 9-inch pastry shell and bake at 350° for 3 minutes.
Pour filling into crust and bake until brown.

title: tex-mex roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Salt and pepper both sides, then place in roaster.
Pour remaining ingredients around roast.
Cover with water.
Place lid on and bake in oven for 12 hours at 250°.

title: angel delight salad
directions: First, dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and juice from pineapple.
Add marshmallows and chill.
Add coconut, pecans and pineapple.
Fold in whipping cream and chill.
May use any flavor Jell-O.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Chop broccoli, set aside.
Cook and stir garlic in hot oil in large skillet over medium high heat until lightly browned.
Add broccoli.
Cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cheeses, butter, broth and wine.
Simmer until cheeses melt.

title: chicken cord-don bleu
directions: Take one chicken breast half, lay flat.
Put 2 slices of ham on chicken, then put one piece of cheese on ham folded up.
Roll chicken with ham and cheese in middle.
Place a toothpick through chicken to hold together.
Continue until all chicken is rolled. Place in greased cake pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk until mixed well, pour over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 round pans.
Slice each in half.
Mix pudding as directed; fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and put bananas in juice.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix until smooth.
Shape into two balls; chill.
Garnish one ball with finely chopped almonds and the other with chopped parsley.
Surround with ripe and stuffed olives and crisp crackers.

title: chicken breast ginger
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam on heat of medium. Add chicken; cook on medium 8 to 10 minutes until tender. Drain peaches, reserving juice. Add water to equal 1/2 cup. Stir in cornstarch, ginger and salt. Add to skillet which chicken was removed from. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more. Gently stir in peaches and water chestnuts.
Heat through. Cook rice. Place on serving dish.
Place chicken next, then spoon peach mixture on top. Serves 4.

title: banana bread(easy)
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and bananas.
Stir in soda, salt and flour.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This freezes well and is moist.

title: pickled red onions
directions: Place onions in a saucepan with the vinegar and enough cold water (about 1 cup) to cover.
Add sugar, cloves and peppercorns. Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes or until the onions are tender.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add water, bouillon cubes, garlic powder and noodles.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Simmer for 4 minutes.
Add Velveeta.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Turn the heat off because as it sets, the pasta will continue to cook and become too mushy.
Use pasta twists or elbow, not egg noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon.
Add tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Break bread up in chunks and add.
Sometimes I leave out the bacon and add butter.

title: hot shoestring potato salad
directions: Soak potatoes in cold water 15 minutes; drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange potatoes in a single layer in a large shallow pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Combine potatoes, bell pepper and green onions in a medium bowl.
Combine vinegar and hoisin sauce in a small bowl.
Pour over potato mixture, tossing gently. Sprinkle with sesame seed and serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: nacho bean dip
directions: Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan, placing beans on bottom up to taco sauce.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: delicious old fashioned banana nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl add eggs, beat well with a large spoon; add honey and butter, blend thoroughly; add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until a toothpick comes out clean.
If bread needs to be baked longer, cover with a piece of foil so top does not get too brown.
Turn out onto a rack to cool.
Bread can be wrapped well and frozen for future use. Yields one loaf.

title: swiss 'n chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together; spread on platter.
Spread salsa over top, then layer with sliced tomato, grated cheese, lettuce and black olives; serve with nachos.
A party favorite!

title: corn flake chews
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to boiling stage, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes, stirring with wooden spoon until all are coated with syrup.
Drop by small rounds onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lottie moon cookies(recipe adjusted by jester summers)
directions: Note:
May add a pinch or a "snickern" of salt.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Add milk, soda and flavorings, then add flour.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white almond cream cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Add butter and 1 cup milk; gradually turn speed on mixer to high and beat 1 minute.
Stop and scrape bowl, then add egg white, remaining 1/2 cup milk and almond flavoring. Beat on high speed for 1 minute or until smooth and fluffy. Pour batter into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: best way for canning corn
directions: You will also need pint jars.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Moisten in milk.
Coat with seasoned flour mixture.
Fry in hot shortening until brown.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain in colander.
In a medium bowl, toss hot tortellini with vinaigrette; cool 10 minutes.
Add cucumber, tomato and onions; toss gently to coat.
Serve at room temperature or refrigerate until serving time.
Serve on lettuce lined plate.
Garnish with oregano sprigs and cherry tomatoes.

title: bratbrick shortbread
directions: Sift flour and cornstarch into a bowl.
Add softened butter and sifted sugar.
Rub butter, flour and cornstarch between your thumb and finger until it resembles crumbs.
Knead mix until it comes together to form a ball.
Press dough with hand into 8-inch round cake pan and stab all over with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter over top; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until firm.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: southern sweet potato pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom only of a bread pan. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and spices in a mixing bowl.
With a spoon, stir in sugar, eggs, oil and milk; stir to blend.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Combine in large bowl the sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa, oil and water.
Pour mixture over sugar and flour and stir.
Then add buttermilk, beaten eggs and vanilla and stir.
Pour into well greased and floured pan (9 x 12-inch) and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: s'mores(by marguerita mccormick)
directions: Place 4 squares of milk chocolate candy bar on a graham cracker.
Top with marshmallow.
Place on a napkin.
Microwave 15 to	20
seconds on High until marshmallow puffs.
Top with another graham cracker.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Combine melted butter, sugar and a few drops of red food coloring.
Add rhubarb; toss lightly.
Spread in 8-inch square cake pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Remove cake from oven; invert.
Let syrup drain onto cake 5 minutes before removing cake pan.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix together and make as you would regular pancakes. Makes 15 (3 to 4-inch) pancakes.

title: apricot citrus salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jello, add dissolved gelatin to hot Jello.
Stir well.

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Take salmon and put into bowl, liquid and all.
Add eggs and mix real good.
Add enough flour to make stiff, but not too stiff. In a skillet, put a small amount of oil and sprinkle with a little meal.
Put spoonful of salmon in skillet and cook until brown on one side.
Turn and cook on other side until brown. Remove and eat.

title: lime-cabbage salad
directions: Make jello according to package
directions; add other ingredients, except dressing, tomatoes and cucumber.
Mix last 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve jello with dressing on the side.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Season well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate crunch
directions: Work with hands first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water; drain.
Mix macaroni, pizza sauce, oregano and garlic salt together in casserole dish; smooth evenly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place pepperoni on top of cheese.
Heat until the cheese melts and serve.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: In mixer, blend pineapple, sugar, flour, eggs, soda and walnuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer in a dish in this order:
egg noodles (cooked), can of mushroom soup, 1 pound hamburger (cooked and drained), 1 can of pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Heat through and serve.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender.
Stir in chicken broth, zucchini, corn, green chilies, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk; heat until hot.
Add cheese.
Makes 5 or 6 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix flour with water until creamy.
Add eggs, Eagle Brand, salt, vanilla and sugar; mix well.
Crumble Butterfingers real fine and add to ice cream mixture.
Add milk and pour into ice cream can.
Freeze.
This recipe is for a 6-quart freezer.

title: bloody mary salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a container and shake well.
Pour over green salad.
Keep refrigerated.

title: one-pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir oil, bananas, vanilla, eggs, baking mix, sugar and nuts in pan with a fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.

title: creamy chicken pie
directions: *Add one more cup broth and 1 more can soup if gravy is desired.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: pink fizz
directions: Chill the cherry soda, cola beverage and cream soda.
Pour beverages into a punch bowl.
Add large scoops of ice cream. Serves 32 punch cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In buttered baking dish, put a layer of crushed chips.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Put layer of this mixture, then layer of chips, layer of tuna mix with layer of chips last in dish.
Bake at 400° until brown and bubbly.

title: delicious southern fried chicken
directions: Cut up and sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken pieces.
In separate container, mix eggs with milk and Worcestershire sauce. Dip chicken in this mixture, then flour it well.
Then place it in the frying pan that has been preheated to 350°.
Cook about 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: white bread
directions: Cook milk, sugar, salt and shortening on stove until shortening is melted, then set aside to cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. In bowl, add 1 cup flour and mix with hand mixer.
Then pour in yeast, stir with spoon and add remaining flour.
Mix well with hands.
Let rise in bowl for 1 hour.
Put in greased loaf pans to rise.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: black bean soup over rice
directions: Coat a nonstick pan with a cooking spray.
Heat the olive oil in the pan.
Add the onion and garlic; saut until translucent. Add the chicken stock, 2 1/2 cups of the cooked black beans and the Creole seasoning.
Bring the mixture to a gentle boil and cook until the amount is reduced by 1/3; puree in a blender or a food processor until smooth.
You may refrigerate this now for serving later.
Then reheat the bean puree.
If necessary, thin the puree with additional chicken stock to make it smooth.
When serving, place cup of the cooked brown rice in each of six bowls.
Top with 1/4 cup of the reserved whole black bean puree.
Squeeze 1/2 lime over each bowl.
Garnish with a cilantro leaf, if desired.
Makes six servings.

title: mrs. king's icing
directions: Use electric mixer to mix oleo, Crisco, sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add milk and 1 tablespoon flour; mix.
Add last tablespoon of flour and vanilla.
Beat until it is light and peaks form. (Total mixing time is 10 minutes.)
Spread over cake, then sprinkle with mini chocolate chips all over icing.

title: pistachio pudding pie
directions: Beat with mixer until thick the first 3 ingredients; pour into crust.
Beat together 1 cup heavy whipping cream and sugar; beat until creamy (do not overbeat).
Pour over pudding mixture and refrigerate 2 hours; serve.

title: quick and easy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter.
Place ingredients directly in pan in layers beginning with melted margarine.
Next sprinkle graham cracker crumbs, followed by layers of coconut, chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk over other ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and loosen edges with knife.
Cool. Cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: nine layer salad
directions: With a clear salad bowl, layer shredded lettuce, chopped green pepper, sliced scallions, sliced celery, cooked frozen peas, mayonnaise with a little sugar and shredded cheese.
When served, top with crispy cooked bacon bits.
Good!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook covered at low heat until broccoli is tender. Pour into casserole dish.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Mix together the sugar, flour, eggs and salt; add pecans.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread marshmallows all over top.
Put back in oven for 2 to 4 minutes to melt marshmallows.
Cool before icing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter lightly a casserole pan.
Pat into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put ketchup on top during last 15 minutes.

title: bessie burgers
directions: Mix ground beef, soup mix, garlic salt, seasoned salt and pepper together.
Make into patties and cook.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; bake in greased cake pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Cook mostaccioli and set aside.
In large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste, undrained mushrooms, water, sugar, basil and bay leaf.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in mostaccioli.
Turn half of the meat mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Layer half of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes.
Remove foil.
Cut remaining Mozzarella cheese into strips; arrange on top of casserole.
Bake about 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: reunion casserole
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, green peppers, corn, soup, tomato sauce, olives, garlic, salt and noodles.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
