Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°. Serves 12.

title: apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Spray pan with Pam before filling with batter.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix flour, butter, salt and sugar together.
Mix in 2 egg yolks.
Add rhubarb and mix.
Fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla in bowl until creamy.
Mix in eggs.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Add mix-ins; stir well.
Drop batter by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, until golden.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a full boil. Stir constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until well blended. Cool.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces and cook as directed.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter until fluffy; add sugar and salt. Continue to beat until light and well blended. Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add chocolate (that has been melted in microwave) and vanilla; blend until well mixed. Pour into shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put half of mixture in warm greased black skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on top, then add remaining mixture.
Bake at 450 degrees for 30 minutes,
Then sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook all day or night.

title: tijuana taco salad(good diabetic recipe)
directions: Brown ground turkey and onion in a skillet; drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, cumin and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup of berries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Add cut up berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear. Stir in food coloring and cool.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for top of pie.
Pour into shell.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream and reserved berries.

title: sweet spiced pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers.
Place in bowl with salt and 3 cups water. Let stand 24 hours.
Rinse in cold water, then in boiling water. Drain.
Pack cucumbers in hot sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to rapid boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 pints.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add milk and egg; beat for 1 minute.
Add shortening and beat 1 minute longer.
Bake in well-greased pan at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: crispy rice jack-o-lantern
directions: You also need a 12-cup bowl.

title: clarksdale squash
directions: Line a buttered casserole with stuffing, minus 1 cup. Mix other ingredients without breaking up squash slices and pour in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
May be made a day ahead and baked when needed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If nuts are omitted add an additional 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: glorified macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix all ingredients except crackers. Crumble crackers over top.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: ham-cheese-broccoli brunch casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; remove crusts from bread and fit into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer in cheese, broccoli and ham.
Arrange the rest of bread to cover entire dish. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; add cocoa and stir until cocoa is dissolved. Add sugar and milk. Stir and bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for one minute. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted. Stir in oatmeal and vanilla. Quickly drop by tablespoon on waxed paper lined cookie sheets. Let cool.

title: easy cheese pie (quiche)
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and flour and place in well-greased pie plate (glass or aluminum).
Beat milk, eggs and pepper until well mixed.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13 pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: flonnie coffin's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Stir in flour. Pour into tube pan, well floured and greased. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Stir well and chill.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, cut up lettuce, celery and onions.
Add peas and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with bacon tidbits and the eggs.

title: homemade dog treats
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Makes a great dip for all fruits.

title: creme puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boiling point.
Sift flour and salt in boiling liquid. Stir until a ball is formed which slips from the side of pan.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg is added.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Place dough 3-inches apart.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 400° for 25 minutes. When baked, remove from sheet to cooling rack; slit on one side to fill.

title: favorite potatoes
directions: Place frozen potato patties in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat margarine and milk together.
Pour over potatoes; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Halfway through baking, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and continue baking.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into meatballs.
Place in baking dish and pour syrup mixture over balls.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add juice and mix.
Tie with thread in a coffee filter, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Let float in mixture.
Simmer on low for 1 hour, but don't boil.

title: dingbats
directions: Combine butter and sugar; add beaten egg with dates.
Cook on low heat until dissolved.
Add pecans and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and then Rice Krispies, mixing well.
Form into balls and roll in flaked coconut.

title: tzimmes deluxe (great for thanksgiving)
directions: Put yams, carrots, prunes and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until tender.
Add apple and honey and cook 25 minutes longer.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Turn mixture into a heatproof serving dish and bake uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: shortbread bars
directions: Mix flour and granulated sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in 1/2 C butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 1 cup juice, and pineapple chunks.
Place in pan.
Cover with cheese, then crackers, then margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry-chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup of sugar and egg yolks.
Stir in flour.
Press evenly in pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Immediately sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips; let set about 5 minutes or until chips are softened.
Carefully spread over baked layer. Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer assorted greens, then spread the mayonnaise over the greens.
Next a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese over mayo.
Then sprinkle entire pack of peas, another sprinkle of cheese, then diced onion, next hard-boiled eggs, next bacon bits and next diced tomato.
Finish off with remaining cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours to overnight.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Add cocoa. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a small mixer bowl; cool completely.
Add powdered sugar alternately with milk, beating to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix ingredients, then add confectioners sugar (about 2 cups). Mix until right consistency.

title: german chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Press into bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; set aside.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and butter or margarine; cook covered for 20 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add cream cheese, beef bouillon cubes, milk, sherry and dill.

title: mexican tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef; drain.
Add seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat shells in oven 5 to 7 minutes.
Fill shells with meat, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Top with taco sauce for added flavor.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and pack into pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: evie's fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, but reserve a few cherries for decoration.
Turn into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 225° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cake is done when no milk oozes out when pressed with fingers.
Decorate with cherries.
Let cool. Store in refrigerator or freezer for about a month.

title: round or flank steak roll
directions: Combine crumbs, onion, suet, salt, pepper and sage.
Moisten with butter.
Spread over steak.
Roll and tie in several places with cord.
Steam until tender at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Brown at 450° for 15 minutes.
Carve across grain for serving.
Serves 6.

title: my grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, blend dry ingredients.
Beat dry ingredients into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on heavily floured surface.
Cut out with an open cookie cutter. Bake on an ungreased sheet for 12 minutes at 375°.
(These kind don't spread when they bake; instead they rise up.
They are a soft sugar cookie I remember from an early age at my favorite grandmother's house.)

title: cheese ring with preserves
directions: Mix and form into ring; fill middle with strawberry preserves. Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in milk, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Spread batter in 6 1/2 x 10-inch baking dish. Cover with pie filling.
Combine lemon juice with boiling water and carefully pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until cake reverses itself and crust top appears.
Put Cool Whip on top (or vanilla ice cream).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Spray an oblong baking dish with Pam.
Brown meat.
Add seasonings and peppers; set aside.
Then add all other ingredients, except cheese, in a bowl.
Pour half of mixture into pan, then top with meat mixture and half of cheese, then repeat corn meal mixture and cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: soft chicken tacos
directions: Combine chicken breasts, basil and salsa in a medium bowl, tossing well to combine. Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla. Microwave each taco at High 30 seconds or until warm. Top each taco with 2 tablespoons of tomato, 1 tablespoon cheese, 1 tablespoon avocado and 1/2 teaspoon sour cream; fold in half. Makes 4 servings.

title: devil dogs
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add sour milk and boiling water all at once.
(Mixture will be watery.)
Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa.
Add all at once to mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for about 5 minutes or until done.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately and let cool.
Put flat sides together with filling.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill overnight in fridge.
Roll dough in balls and flatten on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in the nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven about 12 minutes.

title: costa di crema(lemon cream tart)
directions: Grate rind of the lemons and squeeze 1/4 cup juice.
Beat together 2 egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar, lemon rind and juice. Transfer to a double boiler and stir over simmering water until slightly thickened.
Let cool.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches
directions: In Dutch oven, combine meat, onions, chili powder, salt, water, ketchup and vinegar.
Cover and simmer for 4 hours or until meat falls apart easily.

title: oven potatoes
directions: In a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer the potatoes and onion. In a small bowl, combine the butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder; drizzle over potatoes and onion. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; stir gently to combine. Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Uncover; sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Cut beef into 10 to 12 rectangles, each about 4 x 3-inches. Cut each pickle into 3 to 4 length wise spears.
Sprinkle beef lightly with salt and pepper, and spread a small amount of prepared mustard on each rectangle.
Place pickle strip at narrow end of rectangle; then top it with 1 tablespoon each of chopped onion and bacon.
Roll up beef tightly.
If desired, secure with toothpicks or string.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Sift flour and cocoa.
Combine all in order given and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
As soon as cake is done, spread a small package of miniature marshmallows on top.
Put back in oven until they melt.
Sprinkle with nuts and then cover with frosting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss apples with first 4 ingredients.
In food processor, toss next 3 ingredients together by tossing butter pieces, one at a time, into flour and brown sugar.
Sprinkle this mixture on top of the apples. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until topping is browned.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cook ham in a crock-pot, on a stand.
Save drippings and freeze.
Discard all fat after freezing.
Leave lots of meat on the bone for the beans.
Soak the beans overnight in a crock-pot. Rinse and drain.
Return to crock-pot with picnic bone, onion, pepper and water to cover; add picnic drippings to taste.
Cook until beans are tender.
Remove meat from bone and return to pot. Discard bone.
Cabbage is optional.
Prepare as much rice as needed.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Brown chops well on both sides.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a cup.
Spread half of the potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Add layer of onion rings.
Sprinkle some of the flour mixture and 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Then add the rest of potatoes, onion rings and flour mixture.
Add milk to the other half can of soup.
Mix well and pour over potatoes.
Place pork chops on top. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven or until chops and potatoes are tender.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Add sugar, orange rind, liquid, oil and beaten egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hearty mushroom and beef soup
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms.
In large pot, heat 2 tablespoons oil until hot.
Add mushrooms and saute until golden. Remove from pan and set aside.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Ground beef should be browned, then drained.
Add water, spices and sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Begin layering in casserole dish.
Begin and end with meat sauce.
Meat sauce. 2.
Cottage cheese.
Mozzarella.
Noodles.
Meat sauce.
Repeat all layers and end with meat sauce.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove cover and add additional cheese and bake, uncovered, until melted and slightly brown.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix Kool Aid, sugar, and cold water.
Add sliced lemons. Refrigerate overnight.

title: dark raisin bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and soda in large bowl; let cool.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
When cool, add beaten egg and oil to raisins and water.
Add dry ingredients and mix until wet (do not overmix).
Equally pour into 3 greased 1 pound cans or loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes and remove onto rack, until cold.
Wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator.
Bread will keep for months if kept tightly wrapped.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish, trying to cover bottom of pan without stacking meat (9 x 13 x 2-inch is best).
Salt and pepper.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add egg, oil and milk. Coat each wiener with flour and insert onto a cooking fork or a wooden skewer.
Dip into corn meal mixture, coating all sides. Fry a few at a time in hot fat until golden brown.
Serve with mustard, catsup or chili sauce.

title: diabetic cream puff shell
directions: Melt margarine in boiling water, add flour all at once, stirring well. Add eggs, one at a time while beating well after each addition Spoon onto ungreased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Lower oven to 400° and continue baking for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Open oven door, let cool in oven. Fill with sugar free pudding.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Take 2 cups boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon salt and 2 teaspoons Crisco. Mix together and let cool. Mix together 1/4 cup lukewarm water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar. Add to first mixture. Add beaten eggs and stir in 8 cups flour. Beat thoroughly. Not necessary to knead. Brush top of dough with shortening. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator until double in size. Take out and shape to suit yourself. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes when risen.

title: buttered baked potato slices
directions: Pare and slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Pour half the melted oleo into a shallow baking dish.
Place sliced potatoes into dish. Baste well with part of the remaining oleo.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, flour and cornmeal lightly with fork.
Add eggs, butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until well set.

title: frosty fruit float
directions: Pour juice into a tall glass.
Add ice milk.
Fill with club soda.
Stir and serve.
Yummy and refreshing.

title: martha's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes only 10 minutes with jackets on; cool.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter or oleo and add cream. Grate the cheese.
Layer potatoes, cream mixture and cheese in 3 layers.
Top with fresh bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix, milk, 2 eggs and onion.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Spread in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon evenly over batter in dish.
Bake until set, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn for 3 minutes in boiling water; cool.
Cut from cob. Cook ingredients together for 20 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: idaho potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, cool and dice in a large bowl.
Add cheese, pimento, green pepper, onion, bread, salt, parsley and garlic. Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Turn into a shallow baking dish. Pour melted butter and milk over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: can opener salad
directions: Combine and chill overnight.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Melt bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over very low heat. Beat remaining 1/2 cup butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Top will be quite dark.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely. Frost if you wish.

title: steak on a stick
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large shallow dish.
Add steak; cover and marinate at least 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain steak.
Add honey to reserved marinade.
Thread steak on bamboo skewers.
Grill 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness is reached.
Baste with marinade.
Makes 4 servings.

title: svestka knedlik(plum dumpling)
directions: Mix milk or water to make a dough.
Knead a little. Roll out and cut 3 to 4-inch squares to cover plums.
Take one square and roll up plum in it, sealing off edges to make round.
Drop dumplings into boiling water with a little salt in it.
Cook until tender.
Drain well.
Pour melted butter over dumplings and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; cool off, then add Worcestershire and shrimp.
Stir together.
Cool in refrigerator for 5 hours.
Serve with crackers on the side.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown beef; pour off drippings.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels, then break into small pieces.
Pour off grease in skillet and saute onion.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix together eggs and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in sheet cake pan for about 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: smoothest divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to firm ball stage (248°) or until a small amount of syrup forms a firm ball which does not flatten when dripped into very cold water.
Just before syrup reaches 248°, beat whites until stiff, but not dry.
Pour about half of the syrup slowly over the egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remainder to a soft crack (272°) or until a small amount of syrup separates into threads which are hard, but not brittle.
Add syrup slowly to the 1st mixture, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts or fruit.
Drop from spoon onto foil.
Makes approximately 1 3/4 pounds.

title: spinach and clam soup
directions: Heat skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion, bacon, anchovies and garlic; saute lightly.
Remove mixture from heat.

title: south-of-the-border pie
directions: In a skillet, cook the onion in hot oil until tender.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and salt.
Cook 1 minute more. Cool.
Stir in beans, rice, cheese, milk, eggs and hot pepper. Spray a 10-inch pie plate with Pam.
Put rice mixture in pie pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until center is set. Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Squeeze moisture out of spinach.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to jello.
Add everything else. Pour in half of mixture to mold.
Allow to chill.
When firm, spread 1 pint sour cream or yogurt over jello.
Pour remaining jello on top.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: she crab soup
directions: Mix soup, butter and half and half cream until smooth.
Add crabmeat and other ingredients as listed over low heat. Stir constantly. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: zip-quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: In food processor, mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt 15 seconds.
Store in Ziploc bag until ready to make biscuits.
Then pour in food processor; add shortening and butter.
Process 15 seconds or until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and process a few seconds until it forms a ball.
Knead and shape.
Bake biscuits at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: dietetic banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Stir in sour cream and fold in half of Cool Whip.
In a glass dish, layer wafers, pudding and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: matzoh brie(this is a simple dish, that the family loves!)
directions: Break the matzoh and soak in boiling water for 15 minutes. Drain and squeeze dry.
Add the eggs and the salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter with onion, salt and pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients and place in a glass casserole.
A little paprika may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If dry, add a little water.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, melted margarine and vanilla.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: broadway bourbon balls
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate with corn syrup and bourbon over 1 inch simmering water.
Stir in wafers, nuts and powdered sugar.
Shape into one tablespoon balls.
Roll balls in mixture of sugar and ground chocolate.
Let sit overnight before eating. Store in tightly covered container.

title: green tomato salad
directions: Let peppers, onions and tomatoes stand in salt water for 2 hours.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours and can.
Process.

title: reeses pieces cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla then eggs. Mix in the flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in the Reeses Pieces.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake 8-10 minutes.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together with electric mixer.
Drop by spoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water 4 - 5 minutes, drain well and put in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Mix chicken, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and curry powder. Pour on top of broccoli, sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 325° for 1 hour.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Mix ingredients in a punch bowl.
Add ice cubes.
Garnish with slices of orange and lemon.
Cherries are optional.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and water in 5-quart pan.
Tie allspice and cloves in cheesecloth. Put this and cinnamon into mixture.
Cover and boil 5 minutes.
Peel peaches; drop into boiling syrup a few at a time.
Simmer until tender, about 5 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars.
Cover with syrup.
Seal.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: brown sugar pecan rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine bacon, onion and broccoli.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over.
Marinate 3 hours and serve.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir together thoroughly flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine strawberry jam and yogurt.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Divide batter among five greased and floured 4 x 2 x 1-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
until done, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove from pans. Cool on racks.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar until light and smooth.
Add eggs and blend.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Turn out onto plate; dust with powdered sugar.

title: pizza marghamita
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Allow to proof 5 minutes.
Mix in oil and salt.
Stir in flours until blended.
On well-floured board, knead until smooth and elastic 5 to 15 minutes.
Let rise in covered bowl in cool place for 1 hour.
Knead again briefly. Form into 2 balls.
Flatten each into 14-inch rounds.
Cover with vegetables and cheeses (shredded).
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Cut carrots in pieces, quarter cabbage and cut potatoes in half.
Place all in water to cover and boil.
Simmer until tender.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onion in the margarine.
Add sauces and soups to the onion and meat mixture.
Layer the meat mixture and tortillas in a large 9 x 13-inch casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
You may tear the tortillas into fourths and add them to the mixture instead of layering.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on cookie
sheet
and	flatten
slightly with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can add nuts, but we like them plain.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate, in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate in microwave; pour over cereal mix. Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: veal creole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute green peppers and onion. Brown the veal cutlets which have been dipped in flour and sprinkled with salt and pepper.
When brown, pour over catsup that has been mixed with the warm water.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all but crab meat and cheese.
Mix thoroughly, then mix in crab meat and cheese.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with crackers.
Serves about 20.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the crumbs and put in buttered casserole; top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour liquid over the vegetables.

title: baked brie
directions: Trim off top and 1/3 sides.
Dot with butter.
Top with dried cranberries and whole pecans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use plain or roll in nuts or parsley flakes.
Can be kept for long time in refrigerator.
Let soften before using.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Discard drippings.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt.
Stir well.
Cook meat mixture over low heat 10 minutes. Spoon meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer beans, tortillas and cheeses over mixture.
Pour tomato liquid over cheese.
Chop tomatoes and spread tomatoes and chilies over cheese.
Spread soup over all.
Cover baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in medium oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Blend together peanut butter and margarine.
Add vanilla and honey, beating well.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Place ten cupcake liners in muffin cups.
Fill one half full.
Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 10 cupcakes (1 starch and 1 fat).

title: nanny's barbecue hash
directions: Cook stew
meat
until
done.
Cool and pull apart. Put all ingredients in large pot and cook 1 hour.

title: chocolate coconut pecan cake
directions: Mix and bake cake layers according to directions on cake box. Prepare filling by mixing sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Beat well. Add frosting mix and beat until well blended.
Spread on layers.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add milk, baking powder, soda, vanilla, salt, cocoa, flour and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon (dip in powdered sugar).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Mix peanuts, oats, flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add oleo.
Mix until moistened and resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mix.
Press remaining mix into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Combine all of remaining ingredients, mixture and candies.
Spread over crust to 1/4 inch of edge.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: "b's" cheese ball
directions: Put cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Mix with mixer, cheese and margarine.
Fold in onions and olives.
Roll in pecans. Chill before serving.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Combine crackers, dry Ranch dressing, dill weed, oil and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add dry herbal salad dressing.
Mix again. Cover and marinate overnight or 24 hours before serving.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix 3 tablespoons brown sugar, 1/4 cup catsup, 1/4 cup nutmeg, 1 teaspoon mustard.
Layer sauce over meatloaf and bake 15 to 30 more minutes until done.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread 2 slices of rye bread with dressing.
Place 2 slices corned beef on one slice of the bread and top with two heaping tablespoons of kraut.
Put slice of Swiss cheese over kraut. Cover with other slice of bread.
Wrap in foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 15 minutes or until hot throughout.
(Thousand Island dressing is a choice for this sandwich.)

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Pie:
Butter 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Peel, core and slice apples and put in plate.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Cream 1 stick soft butter or margarine, 1 cup sugar, salt, egg and milk together.
Add flour to creamed ingredients.
Mix and spread over apples.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add and mix vegetable oil, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk soda mixture.
Add and mix chopped nuts and bananas.
Bake approximately 1 hour in a bundt pan or 2 loaf pans at 350.

title: missouri casserole
directions: Peel and slice raw potatoes and put half of them into a greased casserole.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Cover with a layer of 1/2 of the raw ground chuck broken into small pieces and 1/2 of the onion and a little more salt and pepper.
Cover with 1/2 of the tomatoes.
Repeat all layers.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add a little water during cooking, if needed.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine 1/4 cup chicken broth with cornstarch.
Bring remaining 3/4 cup chicken broth, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and sugar to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and simmer until thick (about 2 minutes).
Set aside.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil in large nonstick frying pan.
Add chopped carrots, cover and cook until liquid evaporates, 5 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon scallions and bean sprouts.
Cook until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from frying pan and combine with 1 tablespoon soy sauce, flour, eggs and pepper.

title: t's oyster stuffing
directions: Mix crumbs with butter.
Add oysters and seasonings.
For 16 to 18 pound bird, double the recipe.

title: green bean casserole deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine beans, soup, milk, 1/2 can onions, 1/2 jar bacon bits and pepper; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bacon bits.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat and drain spinach; add butter, cheese, eggs, soup, mayonnaise, milk and water chestnuts.
Place in a greased casserole.
Saute cracker crumbs with butter.
Pour over mixture. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls thin on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Spread with cream cheese, Ranch dressing and sour cream.
Sprinkle garlic salt and Italian seasoning on top.
Press in cubed tomatoes, green pepper, onions, black and green olives, pepperoni, mushrooms or whatever you like on pizza. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Wonderful!

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup pecans and melt oleo and mix for first layer.
Press into bottom of large dish or pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
After it has cooled, blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip for second layer.
Mix instant chocolate pudding and 3 cups milk for third layer.
Spread Cool Whip for top layer.

title: wet burritos
directions: Brown ground beef; add seasoning mix as directed on package. Add chili powder, cumin, garlic and onion powder to beef broth. Bring to boil and thicken with cornstarch or flour and water to make a gravy.
On dinner plate, place a tortilla shell; fill with ground beef and beans (if desired).
Fold shell and place fold side down on plate.
Pour gravy over and top with yellow cheese.
Place a small strip of Mozzarella cheese down middle.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomato, green pepper and onion.
Add salsa sauce and sour cream.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Sift together
the
flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of flour mixture.
Combine milk, egg and oil; add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir	quickly,
just	until
dry ingredients are moistened.	Toss
together	the
blueberries and 2 tablespoons sugar; gently
stir
into batter, along with lemon peel.
Fill greased 2
1/2-inch
muffin
pans
2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25
minutes.	While
muffins are still warm, dip tops in melted butter,
then into a little granulated sugar.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Layer Swiss in bottom of pie shell; add asparagus and onions. Mix eggs, milk, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Put over top. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: dennis scales' peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook for 2 minutes after it starts to boil.
Then add the peanut butter.
Beat well and pour into a buttered pan.

title: corn bread without corn meal
directions: Grease and flour bread pan.
Mix all ingredients together with buttermilk.
May add small amount of water if needed.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450° or until brown.

title: meatballs ala eric
directions: Combine hamburger, sausage, eggs and black pepper.
In separate dish, combine chunky salsa, tomato paste, tomato sauce, oregano, garlic, finely chopped bell pepper, chili pepper, onion and stewed tomatoes.
Mix with meat mixture and bread crumbs until mixture can be shaped into little balls, then roll in leftover crumbs.
Cook in covered frypan; turn once.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 15 minutes.

title: dulce con nueces(brown sugar pralines)
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and cream; mix well.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir in pecans.
Beat about 1 minute or until candy just begins to lose its gloss.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper, shaping into patties with back of spoon.
If the candy becomes too stiff to drop, add a little hot water to make the right consistency.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: liver and vegetable saute
directions: Dip liver slices in flour.
Heat butter in large skillet until bubbly.
Cook liver in butter until brown on both sides, 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except lemon juice. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer covered until liver is done, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Yields 2 servings.

title: hi ho chicken
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, almonds and 1 tube crackers. Put chicken in greased baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over top. Melt oleo and add the other 2 tubes of crackers.
Mix and sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Spread crumbs over top the last 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: scottish banana cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add almond flavoring.
Sift together flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with mashed bananas.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook the chopped onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown. Stir in flour, chicken bouillon granules, mustard, thyme and pepper.
Add milk and water all at once.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.

title: caramel graham crackers
directions: Separate graham crackers and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. In small pan, heat margarine and brown sugar. Boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Add pecans. Spread over graham crackers and place in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake. Use spatula to remove from pan.

title: char siu pork
directions: Cut pork butt into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Combine all ingredients and soak overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in an open pan.
When cooking, pour sauce into pan and cook.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil; add dry Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, nutmeats and coconut. Put in loaf dish and spread Cool Whip over top.

title: snickers bar salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box. Add Cool Whip and place in refrigerator.
Cut up the apples and Snickers bars.
Add to pudding mixture. Chill before serving.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Beat 4 minutes. Add and stir well the 1 cup coconut and 1/2 can drained crushed pineapple. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with Doritos.
Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Pour over chips.
In a saucepan, melt together soup, milk, butter and Ro-Tel.
Pour over hamburger. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: divine chocolate cake(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In small, heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 2/3 cup morsels, stirring frequently until smooth.
Remove from heat.
In small mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in melted chocolate until smooth.
Beat in flour.
Stir in walnuts, orange zest and 2/3 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 9-inch heart-shaped pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 38 to 42 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out slightly moist.
Cool for 20 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Slip wax paper under rack; spread Chocolate Glaze over top and sides of cake.
If desired, place 1 to 2 tablespoons glaze in piping bag filled with small plain tip.
Pipe message and decorate; chill.

title: brown stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or deep stew pan.
Add garlic and meat. Brown meat on all sides.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, bay leaf and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf; add 2 cups water and potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes or until tender, then add canned vegetables.
Heat.
Blend together until smooth 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir into liquid to thicken.
Serve over homemade drop biscuits.

title: magic chocolate swirl cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, 1 teaspoon soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Take out 2 cups of batter and pour the rest in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Add 1/4 teaspoon soda and chocolate syrup to the 2 cups of batter. Beat. Pour in pan over the other batter. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: broccoli-rice-a-roni and chicken
directions: Place Rice-A-Roni in large skillet and brown in small amount of oil.
Add chicken, broccoli (cut in little pieces), flavor packet and enough water to cover broccoli.
Bring to boil, then cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for about 30 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: fourth of july potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Boil in skins until tender.
Peel and dice. (Eggs and potatoes can be boiled together.)
Shell and dice hard-cooked eggs.
In a large bowl, stir together the celery, onion, gherkins, mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt, paprika and pickle juice.
Fold in the potatoes and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Makes about 1 1/2-quarts.

title: fudge - easier to understand
directions: Put first three ingredients in a large kettle and bring to a slow boil.
Once boiling, stir for 4 minutes.
Will stick and burn easily, so must watch and stir frequently while waiting for it to boil.
After 4 minutes of boiling and stirring, remove from the heat and add the milk chocolate, baking chocolate and chocolate chips.
Stir into the first mixture.
Once the chocolate is melted, add the Marshmallow Crme and vanilla.
Mix and then add the walnuts.
Pour into wax paper lined pan, about the size of a broiler pan.
Let cool, then refrigerate or freeze.
Makes about 5 pounds of fudge.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Combine; form into loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: orange breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process mixture until frothy. Serve immediately.

title: fresh raspberry, strawberry or peach pie
directions: Bake and cool pie crust.
Boil sugar and 1 1/4 cups water until the sugar is dissolved.
Mix cornstarch with 3 tablespoons water and add to sugar mixture.
Cook until thick.
I add a little crushed fruit to give it color.
Cool mixture a little, then carefully stir in fruit.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Superb!

title: hot pineapple dish
directions: Pour pineapple and 1/2 cup juice into a baking dish. Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple. Melt butter. Crush Ritz crackers. Mix butter and crushed crackers well. Spread cracker mixture over pineapple and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and immediately add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Stir until mixed, then add flour, vanilla and salt, stirring until well blended but working quickly.
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut to desired size.

title: baked beans
directions: When beans are done, add 1/2 cup white sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour in baking dish.
Add bacon or meat of your choice. Bake at 350° until brown and meat is done (1 hour or more).

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix together.
Slice 2 pans of tiny dinner rolls in half.
Put a layer of thinly sliced ham and a layer of Swiss cheese inside rolls.
Pour butter mixture over the top and let stand at least 1 hour or overnight.
Sprinkle poppy seed over the top. Refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bundles
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets; cut stems in half lengthwise. Need 10 to 12 pieces.
Steam broccoli for 5 to 8 minutes (barely tender).
Wrap broccoli pieces with a thin slice of cheese and ham.
Place in lightly buttered baking dish.
Drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Season with pepper.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: stuffed pumpernickel
directions: Mix ingredients together until soft.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Scoop out bread and fill with cheese mixture.
Put extra pieces of bread on the side for dipping.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients and serve with meats.
This will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk, then add cream cheese and mix (may be a little lumpy, that's okay).
Spread over cake; put pineapple on top of pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with about 1 to 2 cups chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pantry supper
directions: Heat together in saucepan over medium heat until hot.
Serve over Minute rice or toast points.
Serve with fruit salad or lettuce wedges for an almost instant dinner.
Serves 4.

title: chicken roll-ups(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Tear chicken into bite-size pieces. Place small amounts of chicken and cheese on each crescent roll. Roll up and place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick oil.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil and drain.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk, plus soda, then add your flour, oatmeal and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or less.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In skillet, melt butter and cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain well.
Add green peppers to butter and saute until softened.
Remove peppers and drain.
Beat eggs and egg yolks until fluffy.
Add cream and blend well. Crumble bacon and sprinkle over bottom of pie crust.
Repeat with green peppers and half of the cheese.
Add remaining cheese and crab to eggs.
Pour egg mixture into pie crust and season to taste.
Place in oven and reduce heat to 375°.
Bake for 55 minutes or until when knife inserted into center comes out clean. Makes 6 servings.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken or hen and remove meat from bones, cutting meat into bite-sized pieces.
Reserve hot chicken broth and dip tortillas into broth quickly, laying them in an oblong baking dish.
Layer with chicken, chopped green pepper, chopped onion, grated cheese, chili powder, soups and seasonings to taste.
Top with canned tomatoes (Ro-Tel).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Reserve 1 cup for top.
Press remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, mix 3 teaspoons mixture to 1 cup hot water.
May use apricot jello instead of peach.

title: cream cheese sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry sausage and onion until brown.
Drain well.
Add sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in the meat mixture and chill.

title: chicken vegetable noodle soup
directions: Lightly spray a large soup pot with nonfat cooking spray. Pour 2 tablespoons chicken broth into pot and heat over medium-high heat. Add onions, carrots, celery and red pepper and cook 3 to 5 minutes just until tender-crisp. Pour remaining chicken broth into pot. Increase heat to high and bring soup to a boil. Add chicken pieces, noodles, pepper and garlic powder to pot. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender and chicken is cooked through.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, yolks and all flavorings in large bowl.
Mix in flour.
Fold in egg whites. Butter pans(s).
Sprinkle 1/2 nuts on bottom of pan(s).
Add batter, then rest of nuts on top.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, 1 to 1 1/2-inches off oven floor.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: With electric mixer on low speed, mix until crumbly.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to this hot mixture.
Beat eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Pour in cookie sheet pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
The last five minutes of baking make frosting.

title: butter cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, juice, Crisco and cream.
Add flour and baking powder.
Let rest awhile.
Use cookie press to shape cookies.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat margarine and sugar.
Stir in apples, cereal and flour mixture. Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until done.

title: apple and yams
directions: Put in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crumb pie crust
directions: Toss ingredients until crumbs are well moistened.
Press carefully into pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch crust (8 servings), approximately 105 calories per serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix together all ingredients except cheese. Layer broccoli in casserole dish.
Spread ingredients on top of broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hidden treasure strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in fruit and nuts. Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, margarine (melted) and nuts. Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and basil.
In another bowl, beat the egg.
Dip chicken into egg, then coat with crumb mixture.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter and oil over medium heat until juices run clear.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast, warm water and cake mix.
Stir in flour.
Set in a warm place to rise.
Punch down.
Shape into sweet rolls as you desire.

title: easy pumpkin dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Sprinkle with dry cake mix and drizzle with butter. Top with walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Spray 8-inch square baking dish.
Place broccoli in dish. Cook cheese and half of butter in saucepan until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Pour over broccoli.
Toss crackers with remaining butter in bowl; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and put pecans and coconut (mixed) in bottom of pan.
Mix cake in bowl as directed on the box.
Spread over pecans and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Drizzle over cake and bake at temperature given on cake box.
You may need to bake longer until center is done and doesn't stick to a toothpick.
When baked, top has cracks which look similar to an earthquake.
Makes 12 to 18 pieces.

title: mexican chicken 'n dumplings
directions: In large saucepan, boil the chicken.
While chicken boils, mix together both soups in another saucepan.
Cut cheese into blocks and add to soups.
Simmer over medium heat just until soup boils and cheese is melted.
Take chicken out of stock and cut up; add cut-up chicken and soup mixture back to stock.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Add dumplings last; cook about 5 minutes longer or until dumplings are done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Use tomato juice to thin to desired consistency.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and onion. Remove 2 tablespoons sugar and reserve. Add larger portion of sugar to vegetables.
Heat to boiling remaining ingredients and reserved sugar.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Mix well. Store in jars in refrigerator.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Add pudding mix to milk.
Mix slowly with rotary beater at lowest speed just until blended, about 30 seconds.
Blend pumpkin, spice and 2 cups whipped topping.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and pecans.

title: tomato manicotti
directions: Pour 1/2 cup tomato sauce into a 2-quart shallow baking dish; set aside.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook at moderate heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage, then cook 6 more minutes.
Add marshmallows and vanilla. Add nuts; then beat.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions and peppers until done.
Stir in beans and barbecue sauce.
Spread in casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and place over mixture.
Spread cheese over biscuits and meat mixture.
Bake until biscuits are done and cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple and carrot casserole
directions: Slice carrots thinly and cook in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Slice apples and cook in clear water 5 minutes; drain. Layer carrots and apples in casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg and sprinkle over top.
Dot with butter.
Pour orange juice over all.
(Can be made ahead and baked just before serving.) Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chokecherry jelly
directions: Boil juice 1 minute.
Add sugar; bring to a boil.
Add Certo; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim foam.
Pour into hot jars 1/8 inch from top.
Seal and invert jars for 5 minutes.
Turn back over.

title: broiled pineapple with rum
directions: Preheat broiler.
Split pineapple lengthwise.
Remove and cube the yellow fruit, leaving the skin intact.
Toss fruit and rum, then put it back into the "shells."
Wrap the leaves in foil.
Put the filled halves on a broiler pan; sprinkle with brown sugar and broil until sugar melts.
(If pineapple is too close to the heat, the rum will ignite.
Just lower the pan.)
Remove foil and serve at once with ice cream.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Dip up with an ice cream scoop.
Place approximately 5 to 6 scoops on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not press flat.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and store in sealed container.
Serves lots!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients. Put in casserole dish.

title: top of stove meat loaf for 2
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce and water.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Brown in frypan until brown on all sides.
Drain grease.
Add water and tomato sauce (mixed separately) over loaves.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Add more water if needed.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter; fold in cool whip, vanilla and sugar.
Scoop into pie shells; cover with cool whip and drizzle each piece with chocolate syrup before serving.

title: dumplings
directions: Whip egg and buttermilk.
Add to other ingredients and mix. Roll out and let set for 15 minutes.
Cut out and drop in chicken and liquid.

title: orange glaze for cake topping
directions: Cream together all ingredients.
Heat and pour over cool cake or punch holes in hot cake and let run slowly into holes.
Drizzle over cake.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in other ingredients with enough flour to make dough stiff.
Let rise, then make into rolls.
Let rise again, then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: moms hot german potato salad
directions: Mix vinegar into bacon grease until hot.
Add egg yolks.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Add sugar salt and pepper to taste. Add more vinegar if needed.

title: ritz dessert
directions: Mix crushed crackers, coconut, pecans and butter to make crust. Reserve some for topping.
Put crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix softened ice cream, milk, and pudding to form middle layer.
Spread over crust.
Chill.
Spread Cool Whip over and sprinkle reserved topping on top.
Chill and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: champagne raspberry granite
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil in saucepan.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature. Puree raspberries in blender or food processor.
Press through fine sieve into large bowl; discard seeds.
Makes 1 cup.
Add sugar, syrup, raspberry puree and champagne to bowl.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch metal pan.
Freeze, stirring, every 30 minutes, until completely frozen, 3 to 5 hours.
To serve, spoon Granite into chilled wine glasses.
Serve with fresh raspberries and cookies. Makes 8 cups.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Pat remaining mix lightly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: almond fried chicken(chinese style)
directions: Marinate chicken strips in next 6 ingredients for 2 hours. Drain; dip in beaten egg, then dredge in flour.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Arrange on lettuce leaves on serving plate.
Bring to boil the chicken broth.
Add butter.
Make a paste with the cornstarch and small amount of water and add to the boiling broth, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon over chicken and sprinkle with slivered almonds.

title: congo squares
directions: Heat shortening, add sugar.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and chops.
Put into 9x13 baking pan.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in pan.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Slowly add syrup beating constantly.
Beat until it holds shape.
Quickly drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Note:
Weather affects the outcome of this candy.
DO NOT try to make it when it is raining or snowing.

title: ruth's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, except marshmallows.
Add these last. Place in a covered container in the refrigerator. Serve as a salad or as a low-fat dessert.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate (10 inch).
Mix apples and spices.
Turn into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with a hand mixer.
Pour into plate.
Sprinkle with Streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55-60 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil water, margarine and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and soda.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes, butter, onion, green pepper, water, salt and pepper (optional) in large skillet.
Cover; cook, stirring now and then, over low heat for about 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in cheese and milk.
Cover; cook and stirring now and then until cheese melts and mixture thickens.
Do not boil.
Spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle paprika or parsley flakes if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball. Roll in pecans; chill.
Great with Keebler wheat crackers.

title: indian taco
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Season with salt, pepper and chili powder. Add tomato paste, tomatoes and 4 cans water; add basil and oregano.
Break up tomatoes with fork. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve on Indian Fry Bread in layers: meat sauce, lettuce, cheese, raw onion and chilies.

title: hot and spicy chex party mix(microwave)
directions: Mix margarine, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and seasoned salt; mix well.
Pour mixture into Glad-Lock zipper bag.
Seal top of bag securely; shake until all pieces are completely coated. Pour into microwavable bowl.
Put on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool, then eat.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Grease casserole with butter.
Cook potatoes in salt water, mash, but don't add milk.
Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Put into casserole dish and sprinkle heavily with grated Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Refrigerate overnight.
This brings out the flavor.
Take out of refrigerator about 1/2 hour before baking and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or longer, until top is golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch
directions: Blend with electric mixer juice, sherbet and ice cream at low speed until well mixed.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: red pepper-sun-dried tomato pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Toss hot pasta with sauce and serve. Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Bake in a greased loaf pan in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done in the middle.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well. Place in buttered mold. Chill and remove from mold. Roll in pecans.

title: curry soup
directions: Mix all together; serve hot or cold.
Serve 6 people.

title: cereal sundae
directions: Fill bowl halfway to the top with cereal.
Place a large scoop of ice cream in the center.
Sprinkle with a little more cereal.
Serve right away.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until knife inserted into middle comes out clear.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: classic cranberry sauce
directions: Grate all the zest off the orange.
Mix zest with sugar in medium saucepan.
Squeeze juice from orange into measuring cup. Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Pour into saucepan and stir to dissolve sugar.
Heat to a boil.
Add cranberries.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Boil gently until all cranberries pop.
Stir often.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Cool in saucepan.
Pour into serving dish.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 12 x 15-inch pan.
Press seams together.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix and spread over cooled crust.
Chop up any variety of fresh veggies - onion, green pepper, zucchini, carrot, tomato, mushroom, radish, etc.
Vegetables need to be grated or finely chopped.
Sprinkle veggies over cream cheese-covered crust and press in lightly.
Top with grated cheese if desired.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: no bake clark bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Pour in buttered pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: avocado-lemon jello
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Pour into 2 x 8 x 11-inch dish. Add the above ingredients, drained pineapple first, then the rest of the diced and chopped items. Refrigerate until set.
Serve on crisp layers of lettuce. Garnish with heaping teaspoonful of Miracle Whip that has been blended with (equal portion) Cool Whip, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: petits pots de chocolate
directions: Bring milk to boiling.
Add to other ingredients in blender. Blend 1 minute. Chill 2 hours. Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Chop cabbage fine and drop into boiling salted water for about 8 minutes.
Prepare white sauce by combining butter, flour and milk in a saucepan.
Put saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese.
Arrange layers of drained cabbage, white sauce and eggs; repeat.
Top with bread crumbs dotted with butter and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Saute zucchini in 2 tablespoons butter until crisp-tender. Drain off butter; combine other ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in zucchini and remaining butter.
Put in 2-quart ungreased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Cover chicken breasts with waxed paper and pound flat.
Dip in egg; coat with flour.
Saute in butter and remove from pan; keep warm.
Add wine to pan and reduce; add broth and lemon juice.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt; set aside.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: spirit balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Roll into powdered sugar.
Store in tight closed can in refrigerator about 10 days.
Can freeze. Great for Christmas.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Mix boiling water to nuts and dates; let stand.
Put dry ingredients into butter.
Mix, then add nuts and dates.
Grease pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: faye's pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 regular pie crusts. Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This pie is not too sweet.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine ground beef, onion and green pepper in a skillet.
Cook over medium heat.
Drain well.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning; mix well.
Place half the cabbage into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Cover with half of meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted and a golden brown.
(Can be made into mock cabbage rolls by adding 1/4 cup raw instant rice to each layer.)

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in baking dish; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add pineapple and top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar until thick and heavy.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300°.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake for 45 minutes or until knife is clean when tested.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; bone and cut in small pieces.
Prepare wild rice according to instructions on box.
Combine chicken, rice, sour cream French onion dip, pimentos and mushrooms.
Place in greased casserole; sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, flavoring, flour and mix. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Can add pecans or coconut.

title: peach pie
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, mixing well.
Fold in peaches then put in pie shell.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let set 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat well into apple and sugar mixture.
Bake in large tube pan or 3 small loaf pans about 1 hour at 325°.
Can be frozen and kept for quite awhile.

title: white or dark chocolate-covered ritz peanut butter crackers
directions: Spread generous amount of peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
(Continue to do this until you have made your desired amount.)
Melt bark in microwave bowl in the microwave until melted (about 3 minutes).
With a fork, dip each cracker sandwich into the bark.
Let excess bark drain off, then place dipped cracker sandwich onto aluminum foil.
Let cracker sandwiches dry and harden.
Store in an airtight container.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Cut cabbage into small strips and add to meat mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; let simmer for 45 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is cooling, cook brown sugar and pineapple in small saucepan until well blended.
With fork pick cake over top and pour pineapple mixture evenly over it.
Make pudding and pour over cake. Put whipped cream over pudding and then nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
"Yum Yum."

title: egg brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix remaining ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight. Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked apple dessert
directions: Mix 2 cans apple filling with crushed pineapple.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle as much or as little cinnamon as desired on top.
Top with yellow cake mix.
Pour melted butter on top of cake mix until most is saturated.
Bake for one hour or longer, if you want the top more crunchy.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasonings and Ragu. Prepare noodles and drain.
Arrange one layer of 3 noodles in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/3 of meat sauce and 1/3 of the cheese.
Sprinkle on 1 tablespoon of parsley flakes. Repeat layers, ending with cheese and flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken or ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 5.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Stir in honey, eggs and sour cream.
Sift in flours, baking soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.
Cover with a layer of blueberries mixed with half the sugar/cinnamon mix.
Pour in remaining batter.
Top with remaining sugar/cinnamon.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: flank steak roll
directions: Season steak with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Spread uncooked sausage on steak, patting down firmly.
Roll up steak and tie.
Brown in a small amount of cooking oil.
(Electric skillet works best.)
Pour about 1/2 cup sauce over meat.
Cover and cook at low temperature 1 to 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally and adding a little sauce now and then.
Slice to serve.
Sauce may be thickened to a gravy.

title: mary's breakfast souffle
directions: Place bread to cover 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Beat eggs.
Blend in milk, cheese, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add onion.
Pour mixture over the bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Place all of the ingredients in a casserole dish, 15 x 9-inch:
rice, broccoli, onions, celery and oil.
Mix soup, milk, butter and Cheez Whiz together.
Pour over ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop walnut into medium pieces.
Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into greased and lightly floured loaf pans 9x5x2-inches.
Bake on lowest rack at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Can also make 3 small loaves in 8-inch pans.
This bread freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water according to package directions. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onions together.
Blend in broccoli.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on cheese. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: tangy lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually add water, blending until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Remove from heat. Blend about 1/2 cup of hot mixture in saucepan and cook 2 minutes. Add lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.
Serve warm or cold. Sauce may be refrigerated and reheated.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: olive quiche(servings:  4)
directions: *Or grate your own.

title: old-fashioned oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Remove any shell fragments from oysters.
Combine eggs, Worcestershire sauce and reserved liquid.
Add oysters; set aside.
Heat milk to which butter, salt, celery salt and pepper have been added.
When butter has melted, gradually add oyster mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until oysters curl.
Mixture should never boil or it will curdle.
Correct seasonings.
Serve with oysterette crackers.

title: elegant and easy strawberry dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 layer pans, according to directions.
When cool, take 1 layer with serrated knife and cut in half.
Take other layer and freeze for a later time.
Place half layer in bottom of deep bowl, bottom side up (trifle or glass bowl).
Mix pudding according to directions and place 1/2 mixture on top of cake.
Top with 1 package of strawberries.
Place the other 1/2 layer on top of strawberries and repeat with pudding and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberries, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add butter and mix well with fork.
If dough seems dry, work with hands.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover and chill 1 hour or longer.
Heat oven to 400°; bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 3 dozen balls.

title: mvo's 7-4-17 trifle
directions: Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually beat in whipping cream.
Add vanilla and beat until stiff peaks form. Set-aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a buttered 10 x 6-inch baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar with crumbs, cinnamon, nutmeg and oats.
Stir in melted margarine; mix well.
Spread over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave chili con carne
directions: Combine ground beef, garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix well to crumble beef.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, brown sugar, salt, oregano and cumin.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat in boiling water until tender.
Add onion, potatoes, carrots, cabbage and celery, then cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Add seasonings to taste and mix well.
Add green beans and corn; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Cream milk with 1 quart orange drink.
Pour into 4-quart churn; add remaining orange drink.
Put into tub; add ice and salt and turn until frozen.

title: 6 quick rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
