Bake in greased muffin pan until golden brown. Bake at 425°.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, egg, stuffing, nutmeg and 1/2 can soup. Shape firmly into a loaf and place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Blend remaining soup and sour cream.
Heat in pan, stir occasionally.
When meat loaf is done, pour mixture over meat and sprinkle with a little nutmeg.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream margarine or butter.
Add gradually the sugar, creaming well.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each one at medium speed.
Spread mixture in baked pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg, then flour mixture.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Add remaining real lemon juice; pour into pan with chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or longer if desired.

title: chocolate mint surprise
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Separate eggs; beat yolk and add to creamed mixture.
Melt chocolate and add with nuts and vanilla to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Spread over the crumbs and refrigerate for 3 hours. Spread ice cream over all.
Cover and store in freezer.
Cut in squares and serve, topped with whipped cream and maraschino cherry.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Place deboned chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Put Veg-All over chicken.
Mix the cream of celery soup and chicken broth; pour over top of chicken and Veg-All.
Melt butter. Mix flour, milk and butter.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and combine coffee in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low
heat
until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in sugar and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cool and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine bran flakes, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased or paper lined muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 of water. Add remaining water. Add sugar, salt, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Add softened yeast, eggs and potatoes. Beat well. Add flour so dough is soft but not sticky. Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead dough 5 minutes.

title: steve's deer stew
directions: Boil water and deer meat until tender; discard water and add half of potatoes, cut up, and all of the ingredients.
Cook at a low boil until most of the meat and vegetables have broken down, then add last half of potatoes.
Cook 1 hour more.
Total cooking time is about 6 to 8 hours.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Pour over
chicken
and
bake
at
500° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 200° and bake for about 2 hours.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Pound steak thoroughly; cut into serving pieces.
Season.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip meat into mixture, then into cracker crumbs. Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Cover and cook over very low heat for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peachy corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease pie pan - 9-inch round or 8-inch square.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat well for 1 minute.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
(Works best with 9 inch round cake pan.)

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken, reserve broth.
Cool and remove chicken from bone.
Chop into small pieces.
Refrigerate broth until grease hardens.
Lift off and discard; reserve remaining broth.
Mix soup, sour cream, picante sauce, green chilies, onions and 1 cup of broth.
Reserve 1 1/2 cup of this mixture.
To remaining mixture, add diced chicken and 1 cup of grated cheese.
Spoon about 2 Tbsp. of mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll and place in greased baking dish with rolled edge on bottom.
When dish is filled (9 x 13) spread reserved mixture over the top, cover and cook @ 350 degrees for approximately 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle the remainder of the cheese over the top.
Return to oven until melted, about 5 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat
juice
from
cherries
and
pineapple.
Pour over jello. Mix well and cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with a little juice.
Mix pineapple, cherries and pecans. Add Coke to jello and other ingredients.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: crunchy chews
directions: Grease pan.
In saucepan, mix together sugar and corn syrup. Bring to boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Mix in peanut butter.
Turn into prepared pan and stir in cereal.
Press together firmly and cool.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop in food processor.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fairy gingerbread cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs, milk and molasses.
Sift flour, soda, ginger and cinnamon into mixture and beat well.
Last, if desired, add raisins and nuts.
Bake in shallow loaf type greased pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: frosted bread
directions: Remove crusts of bread and cut into 32 cubes.
Beat egg yolk and add to cheese.
Beat with margarine and spices.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg white.
Use toothpick to hold cubes on five sides.
At this point, cubes may be put on a cookie sheet and frozen for up to two weeks.
Place in a 400° oven and bake until puffy and bubbly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Gradually add sugar and mix thoroughly. Break eggs into cream cheese, one at a time, stirring after each. Add almond extract and mix thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake for 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: old fashioned potato cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add
potatoes,
mix
in flour, salt and baking powder.
Add
grated onions and pepper.
Fry in hot buttered pan or in	deep fat until brown on both sides.
Serve with applesauce, crisp
bacon or syrup.
Extra good.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar; beat well.
Add beaten egg yolks. Sift together the flour and spices. Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Add flour mixture and milk alternately. Add remaining ingredients except egg whites.
Stiffly beat egg whites and add last.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in 4 (9-inch) pans in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, milk, flour, salt and egg yolks together until thickened.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into prebaked pie shells.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Put cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Beat egg white until stiff; combine with mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli; broil until golden brown.

title: capirotada(mexican easter bread pudding)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar and water.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Boil until syrup is thickened and syrupy to about 220° on candy thermometer.
Remove cinnamon sticks; keep syrup hot.
Line bottom of baking dish with half of bread.
Add half of apple, then half of cheese.
Sprinkle with all of the raisins and half of pecans.
Pour half of syrup over top.
Repeat bread, apple and cheese layers; sprinkle with remaining pecans and pour remaining syrup over.
Bake in 325° oven until all liquid is absorbed and cheese is melted (about 40 to 45 minutes).
Serve warm or cold, preferably with cream.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: blackberry cobbler*
directions: Combine blackberries, 1 cup sugar and water in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes; stir gently.

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs; blend well.
Beat in anise, flour and baking soda, adding just enough cold water to make a very stiff dough.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add sauces and seasonings; simmer. Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Mix egg with milk and add to sauces.
Makes two layers each of noodles, sauces and cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover at first, then remove to brown cheese.

title: texas hash casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers slowly in shortening. Brown meat and add to onion mixture.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning.
Arrange in large casserole.
Cover and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, folding in whipped cream with vanilla last.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pecan french toast
directions: Place eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla in a bowl and whisk to combine. Mist bottom of a 12 x 8-inch glass casserole with oil spray. Place bread slices in a single layer in the pan. Pour the egg mixture over the bread, distributing it evenly. Turn bread slices once. Cover the pan with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: microwave brunch egg casserole
directions: Microwave bacon on High between several layers of paper toweling 5 to 6 minutes or until crisp.
Cool and crumble. Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper in a bowl.
Beat well.
Pour over croutons and cheese in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Let stand 10 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Sprinkle with bacon and microwave on High an additional 1 to 2 minutes, depending on desired degree of doneness.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up chicken.
Put in a large pot.
Cover with water; salt and pepper to taste.
Add carrots and bay leaves.
Cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; set aside to cool.
Put spaghetti in broth.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until done.
Debone chicken; combine with spaghetti, stir and serve.

title: unstuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Chop cabbage into large pieces.
Place in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Pour off grease.
Stir in raw rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat mixture and cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Watch that it doesn't get too dry.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour. Add coconut to the batter.
Cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: graham streusel
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix crumbs, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Blend cake mix, water and oil with eggs on low speed until moistened, about 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes.

title: golden fruitcake(makes one 5 pound or 3 medium loaves)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Reserve 1/4 cup and set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Combine pecans, pineapple, raisins and cherries plus the 1/4 cup of flour/baking powder reserved before.
Toss gently to coat.
Stir into batter. Spread batter into greased, waxed paper lined 10-inch tube pan (or use 3 loaf pans).
Bake at 275° for
2 hours and 45 minutes or until cake tests done (loaf pans take about 2 hours).
Cool in pan for about 30 minutes.
Remove and continue to cool on rack. Wrap tightly in foil and store in refrigerator or cool room.

title: swedish drommar (dreams)
directions: Beat the butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Combine flour and baking ammonia or cream of tartar and soda.
Add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture and beat until well combined.
Shape the dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place the balls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Using your fingers, press lightly in centers of the cookies.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until done.
Open oven door carefully to avoid fumes if you use baking ammonia.
Makes 80 to 90 cookies.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Blend in sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat in flour until just smooth (no longer).
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done at 325°.

title: creme de menthe
directions: Combine vodka, syrup, peppermint and vanilla in 4-cup screw-top jar.
Stir in enough green food coloring to make bright green.
Close jar.
Store in cool, dark place for 1 month.

title: death by chocolate(makes 24 servings)
directions: Bake brownies according to package; let cool.
Prick holes in the top of brownies with a fork and pour 4 tablespoons of coffee and sugar mixture over brownies; set aside.
Chop candy bars into small pieces.

title: quick quiche
directions: Combine grated cheese and flour.
Sprinkle into pie shell. Top cheese with ham.
Combine eggs, milk and onion soup mix and pour over ham and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato soup. Simmer 10 minutes. Add pork and beans.
Simmer an additional 5 minutes or until beans are heated through.

title: stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into bite size pieces.
Combine flour and sour cream.
Mix in bouillon, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin, vanilla, oil and water.
Add flour mixture a little at a time. Mix well after each addition.
Pour into 2 well floured loaf pans. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crab-stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut out mushroom stems (save for later use) or chop and mix with filling.
Stuff mushroom caps. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put biscuits in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, brown sugar, nuts and butterscotch pudding.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Place on cake plate.

title: christmas tea
directions: Put liquid ingredients in bottom of coffee pot and dry ingredients in basket.
Brew and serve hot.
Use electric percolator.

title: mae's rolls
directions: Beat together the eggs, salt, sugar, baking powder and shortening.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Put yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine and add flour.
Let rise and make at once.
Let rise in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You also need 9-inch flowerpot and artificial flowers.

title: mom's favorite bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour, sugar, butter, milk and salt; mix well.
Let rise; punch down.
Make a loaf and place into a well-greased loaf pan.
Allow to rise again.
Bake in a 400° oven until browned.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple; drain oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: orange jello
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice. Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups. Heat to boiling point. Add jello, cream cheese until smooth. Fold in cool whip and pineapple.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup over low heat.
Remove.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to soup, stirring well.
Add remaining 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into oiled 4 to 5-cup mold and chill until firm.
Unmold and serve with assorted crackers.
Serves a bunch!!

title: custard pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and turn oven to 350°; bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 10 minute peanut brittle
directions: In Corning Ware dish (1 quart) combine syrup, sugar and salt. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave 3 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes until syrup and peanuts are lightly brown.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda. Stir until butter melts and mixture is foamy.
Pour out onto buttered cookie sheet (about 1/4-inch thick).
Let cool.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in lightly salted water until tender; drain. Combine with remaining ingredients, reserving half of the cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for about 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir all together in bowl.
Refrigerate in mold.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice primavera
directions: In a large skillet, cook mushrooms, onions, celery, pepper, bouillon and seasoning in margarine.
Add rice, cheese, peas and carrots. Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Fill 2 loaf pans half full.
Double line pans with wax paper and bake at little over 2 hours at 350°.

title: easy meat loaf(do in microwave)
directions: Grate bread in blender; mix with hamburg.
Grate onion and green pepper in blender; drain and measure.
(A little more or less than 1/2 cup doesn't matter.)
Mix with beaten egg.
Combine these with the meat mixture until well blended.
Add catsup and blend in.
Put into microwave-safe dish (I use a round one) and bake at High setting for 10 to 15 minutes.
(I also spread a little catsup on the top before baking; spread it with a fork.) Best to cover bowl with paper towel to keep oven clean; take off for last five minutes.

title: danish apple slices
directions: Sift flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt.
Cut shortening in with pastry blender.
Put egg yolk into measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to shortening mixture and mix just enough that dough shapes into a ball.
Roll out half of dough into 15 x 11-inch rectangle; transfer to baking sheet.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter and saute mushrooms.
Cut onion into 1/2-inch slices and add to mushrooms.
Saute about 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from pan.
Cut meat into 2-inches long and 1-inch wide slices.
Trim off any fat.
Roll meat into flour and brown in butter.
Add more if needed.
Add mushroom and onion to top of meat.
Mix horseradish, salt, pepper, steak sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple very good.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and chill until firm or overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop onion.
Cook together ground beef and onion until browned; drain.
Combine meat with the cooked rice and onion soup mix; set aside.
Place chopped cabbage in bottom of greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Spread meat/rice mixture over cabbage and top with soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover and continue baking for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a large greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: colonial coffee punch
directions: Add sugar to coffee to taste.
Chill.
Spoon ice cream into coffee.
Serve garnished with whipped topping.

title: velvet salad
directions: Stir until dissolved lemon jello, 1 pint boiling water and marshmallows.
When cool, add pineapple (drained), Cool Whip, salad dressing and fluffy cream cheese.
Put all the mixture in a flat pan.
When set, pour cherry jello (cooled) over top.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt together butter and cocoa.
Remove butter and cocoa from heat; add sugar and egg; mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread the marshmallow cream on the cake.
Spread the frosting over the marshmallow cream.

title: partridge carcass soup
directions: Place carcasses in stew pot, add remaining ingredients, except wine and cream.
Add water almost to cover and bring to boil. Turn down heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Strain the liquid into another pan.
Remove carcasses and set aside.

title: dill sauce
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers, 2 tablespoons or so, and let stand 2 to 3 hours. Drain. Add freshly snipped dill, fat-free or regular yogurt and lemon juice. Mix and let stand until ready to serve. Very good with grilled salmon.

title: rocks(fruit drop cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and butter, adding sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Resift flour along with soda, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and salt.
Add sifted ingredients in 3 parts to the butter mixture, alternately with water or sherry.
Beat the batter until it is smooth after each addition. Stir in fruits.
Drop batter from a teaspoon onto a greased tin. Bake about 12 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Mix and pour over macaroni.
Chill overnight.

title: pizza burgers
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in sauce and oregano.
In a food processor, chop onion, pepper and pepperoni; add to beef mixture.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto buns. Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: kopy kat mounds
directions: Mix coconut and milk together.
Roll into approximately 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate bars and wax in saucepan.
Drop coconut balls into melted chocolate, then place on wax paper to cool.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and other ingredients.
Stir well.
Freeze mixture in 2 plastic containers.
Set out of freezer for 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, mix cereal, nuts, croutons and pretzels.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add cup of cream, lemon and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until puffs up.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat persimmon pulp, soda, sugar and shortening until creamy. Add eggs, dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise. Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to potato mixture and mix well.
Chill until serving time. Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: ice cream pies
directions: Combine cake mix, water, oil and 3/4 cup frosting in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed just until moistened.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes longer or until smooth.
Spread batter over bottoms and up sides of 2 well-greased 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or just until shells test done.
Do not overbake.
Cakes will collapse to form shells.
Cool completely. Beat ice cream in large mixer bowl until smooth.
Spoon into pie shells, leaving a 1/2-inch rim.
Heat remaining frosting in saucepan until soft.
Swirl over top of ice cream.
Freeze, tightly wrapped, for 2 hours or longer.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hanging of the green punch
directions: Make punch in a 1 gallon jar.
Dissolve lime gelatin as directed on box.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Finish filling the gallon jar with cold water.
Pour over ice.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Form small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400° or until lightly brown.
Serve warm.
Freeze leftovers and warm in microwave for a great after school snack.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 2 x 1/4 x 1/8 strips.
Place in 2-quart glass casserole.
Dissolve salt in 1/4 cup water.
Pour over carrots. Cover and microwave at High setting 11 minutes or until carrots are tender, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Drain fruit (need 3 cups of liquid with water and juice). Cook pudding with juice and water until thick.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit.
Let cool in refrigerator, then add Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: beef balls with tomatoes
directions: Mix beef with the eggs, salt, thyme, pepper, garlic, chives and parsley.
Stir vigorously with spoon until mixture stiffens enough to shape into balls.
Shape with hands into 8 balls, about the size of extra large eggs.
Roll balls in flour.
Set aside. (Recipe can be prepared to this point and refrigerated for later cooking.)

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until mixture is smooth.
Serve with hot rolls or muffins.
This may be stored in the refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: baklava
directions: Mix Karo syrup, a few drops of lemon juice and rosewater together and set aside.
In another bowl, add ground nuts together with the sugar and rosewater.
Mix together by hand and set aside.

title: red beans, sausage and rice
directions: Wash beans, cover with enough water and bring to a boil.
Boil approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cold water and drain.
Cover beans with enough water and cook on medium heat until beans are tender, approximately 2 hours.
In separate skillet, saute chopped vegetables.
Add vegetables to tender beans.
Add salt and pepper to taste with smoked sausage.
Let beans simmer at least 1 hour with seasonings.
(If liquid is too thin, add 1 to 2 tablespoons roux.) Cook rice according to directions.
Serve hot over rice.

title: spiced beef stew
directions: Heat heavy casserole with tight-fitting lid over high heat. Trim fatty edges from meat.
Add fat to the hot pan to grease bottom.
Remove pieces and discard.
Cut meat into 2 inch cubes. Brown quickly, stirring.
Sprinkle sugar over meat and brown until the sugar caramelizes (this gives a rich brown color).
Add salt, allspice, bay leaf, cider and beef broth; bring to boiling.
Add carrots and onions.
Return to simmer.
Cover and place in oven. Stir cornstarch into water.
Stir mixture into stew and cook until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dip
directions: Cook hamburger and deer meat, drain.
Add jar of salsa and cheese.
Stir continuously over low heat until cheese melts. Serve with chips.

title: pineapple walnut stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over walnuts.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Drain.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or skillet.
Stir-fry walnuts until brown.
Remove and drain. Add oil as needed.
Stir-fry chicken, garlic, onion and ginger until chicken turns white.
Remove.
Add broccoli.
Stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Return nuts and chicken mixture to wok.
Add pineapple.
Combine syrup, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir into pineapple mixture.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy crab spread
directions: Put cream cheese in a 1-quart dish.
Microwave on Medium 60 to 90 seconds to soften.
Add cheese, sour cream, Worcestershire and mustard.
Stir until well blended.
Gently stir in crab and most of the green onions (reserving some for garnish).

title: crisp pickle mix
directions: Put salt over all vegetables and cover.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours, then drain.
Put in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and can.

title: larry's beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Add chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add hamburger.
Cook until brown.
Cut Polish sausage and hot dogs into 1/2-inch circles and add to hamburger mixture.
Cook until done, about 15 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce and can of soup (no water).
Add drained mushrooms, baked beans, brown sugar and ketchup.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix until creamy.
If too moist, add 1 slice broken bread.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pour over corn and mix well.
Put in two 9 x 12-inch pans. Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: jello punch
directions: In a boiler, heat sugar and water just until the sugar melts. Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, mix 2 parts water to 1 part mix.
For punch that is a little stronger, reduce water.
After adding water, the punch can be put in the freezer for several hours so that is will be slushy.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together and CHOW!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, and soup in an ungreased baking dish. Mix baking mix with milk and egg and pour over top of soup mixture. Bake at 400 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican taco chip dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in round pie plate or baking dish; spread chili on top.
Sprinkle with onion, black olives and taco seasoning mix.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
(Cook only until heated through; be careful not to overcook!)
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandma hager's custard
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Mix in sugar until completely dissolved.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into custard cups.
Set cups in pan of cold water.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash and add butter, salt, milk and garlic salt.
Add cream cheese and sour cream; whip and put in casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook
without stirring the first 3 ingredients to 280°. Add next
3 ingredients and cook to 300°.
Remove from pan and add last 2 ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion. Remove fat. Mix all ingredients together in large microwave dish. Place lid on. Cook on high until hot.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water about 20 minutes.
Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in orange juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Drain apricots and stir into batter with nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in greased and floured bread pan.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Stir in soup, mushrooms and Cheez Whiz; heat through.
Add broccoli and rice. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Remove sausage and leave grease in pan.
Add margarine.
Saute pepper and onion until tender.
Add mushrooms and liquid and cook 5 minutes.
In a saucepan, bring 4 1/2 cups of water to a boil and add soup mix and rice.
Cook for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vegetables and sausage; mix well.
Put into a casserole or crock-pot to keep hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges, apples and orange peeling. Dissolve jello like you always do on package.
Add sugar.
When jello starts to get quivery, add fruit and mix together.
Put in long 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; mix with 1/2 cup butter.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze.
Cut ice cream into 8 sections; let thaw 20 to 30 minutes.
Spread over cookie layer and freeze.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and boling water.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 50 minutes or until pie is solid.

title: "out of this world" pie
directions: Cook pie filling, sugar, pineapple (with juice) and cornstarch until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add dry Jell-O.
Mix well. Cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: mama millie's meatball soup
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together.
Roll into bite size meatballs.
Do not fry; set aside.
Into the 3 quarts water, add the bouillon cubes and beef broth.
Add the onion, carrots, celery and parsnips (if desired) to broth mixture.
(May add more water and broth.)
Simmer vegetables for 1/2 hour, then add meatballs, 2 tablespoons grated cheese and the sauce for color.
Simmer for 1 hour.
If desired, may add 1 cup cooked barley or rice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into an ungreased 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan, then add the vinegar and vanilla, salad oil and cold water.
Stir until no lumps remain.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rare roast beef(from "virginia hospitality")
directions: Roast must be at room temperature!
Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub roast with seasonings.
Place on rack in roasting pan, rib side down.
Roast 1 hour.
Turn oven off!
Do not open oven!
Roast must remain in oven for at least 3 hours and no more than 5 hours. Before serving, turn oven on to 375° and roast for an additional 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not open door!
At the end of the roasting time, remove roast and allow to cool 15 minutes before caring.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixing bowl, cream butter and add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to cream mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden.
Cool at room temperature for about 1 hour and serve.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O with one cup of boiling water.
Put in blender. Add Jell-O, cream cheese and pineapple.
Pour into bowl and add Cool Whip.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Cut whole package of rolls in half through middle like a sandwich.
Spread mixture on top and bottom like a sandwich.
Place layer of ham and Swiss cheese.
Put top back on. Can put back in original package and freeze.
To heat cover with foil and bake 30 minutes on 350°.
Cut a part with sharp knife. Makes 60 little sandwiches.
They always make a hit.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Add pineapple with juice and the pie filling.
Refrigerate until jelled.
In mixer, put sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumber(s).
Mix mayonnaise and vinegar together until creamy.
Add the milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, 1 egg and milk; beat until smooth. Chill until firm enough to handle, about 30 minutes.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls, ovals or logs.
Roll in decorations.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cheese, macaroni and broccoli salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Place in a bowl with a tight fitting lid.
Chill.
Sprinkle a little grated cheese on top of salad before serving.

title: cheesy chicken and rice skillet
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cover. Cook 4 minutes on each side or until cooked through. Remove chicken from skillet. Add soup and water to skillet. Stir. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice and 1 cup of the Velveeta. Top with chicken. Sprinkle with remaining Velveeta. Cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical fluff salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and Jell-O. Fold in Cool Whip. Fold in fruit. Refrigerate.

title: bread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except water. Distribute butter evenly through bread crumbs. Add hot water slowly and keep mixing until the crumbs are moistened. The amount of water added will determine the moistness of the cooked dressing. This recipe makes enough for 2 people. Adjust accordingly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put chips in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Mix beans with 1 cup cheese and 1/2 cup salsa.
Spread on top of chips.
Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning.
(You may use cooked chicken instead of beef.)
Spread this over bean mixture. Top with remaining cheese and green onion. Bake for 10 minutes.
Put sour cream and chopped tomato on before serving.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls(can be made in less than 1 hour)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 1/2-quart bowl; add sugar, oil, salt and egg.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup of flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth and place on rack over bowl of hot water; let rise 15 minutes.
Grease roll pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch or muffin tins) with butter.
Stir down batter; add 1 1/2 cups flour (remaining).

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce and meat balls
directions: Place sauce ingredients in crock-pot and turn to high.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Thoroughly combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk or cream.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven at 325° for about 40 minutes or until mixture doesn't adhere to knife.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with sweetened whipped cream.
Enjoy.

title: mushroom saute
directions: Cut mushrooms into quarters.
Spray large skillet with no-stick spray.
Add chicken broth.
Then add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes, until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in rosemary or oregano to taste, along with pepper and salt.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Pour mixture over melted oleo in 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Thoroughly mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Gradually stir in lemon juice.
Add crumbled cheese; blend well.
Stir in milk, adding more if needed to thin to desired consistency.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
(Blue cheese may be substituted for Roquefort.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and use a teaspoon to dip batter.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
